    <item>
      <title>How to Remove a Curse</title>
      <link>https://www.scribblehub.com/series/1123912/how-to-remove-a-curse/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">3fa1d3101f04620385ef731281969040511db915</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 25 Jun 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Prince Alexander Capet arguably has everything he could ever want. He has a comfortable lifestyle, he's set to rule over a kingdom, and he's even recently proposed to his childhood love, Alice Atkin. For some reason though, something feels a bit...wrong to him. There's an itching there, no matter what he does. He feels as if he can't possibly live up to the expectations placed on him from everyone around him, but has no idea what to change...until one fateful day.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Upon running into a woman who claims to be a "witch," he's told that he has been cursed, and that the only way to remove said curse is through true love. Obviously, he takes this with a grain of salt, but perhaps there might be a benefit from hearing her out. At the very least, if he requires his true love, it's a good thing he's already found her through his fiancé. Who else could it possibly be?&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;First you find said curse…&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;div class="sp-wrap sp-wrap-default"&gt; &lt;div class="sp-head" title="Expand"&gt; Spoiler &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="sp-body folded"&gt; &lt;p&gt;Content warning for gender dysphoria and discomfort from intimacy. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;div class="spdiv"&gt;[collapse]&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Alex couldn’t help but swipe at the poor branch that had been unfortunate enough to be in his way. He didn’t know where he was going at that moment, but he certainly wouldn’t let anything or anyone stop him from getting there. The peaceful nature of the forest that the young Prince had become well acquainted with did nothing to calm his frayed nerves as he delved deeper into the lush realm. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Leave it to him to find a way to snap in front of Alice like that. He had been doing so well, he had been trying so hard, but of course he found a way to mess things up again. He couldn’t just keep his cool for a little bit longer. Once the wedding happened, everything would be fine and he would be content. Everyone feels pre-wedding jitters, but no, he couldn’t have just held them back. It didn’t help that as the days continued on, more and more dread piled up within his mind, feeling as if he was waking up to the dull and depressing ringing of a bell that got louder each and every day. As the day he was to wed Alice got closer and closer, his heart felt more and more as if it was about to deflate.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;It wasn’t that he didn’t wish to get married or fall in love, far from it. Alex had always been obsessed with romance and anything to do with it as far back as when he was a child. He would always beg his mother to tell him stories about people finding their true love and their happily ever after together. He didn’t even mind that he was rather pressured by his family to marry Alice. She was perhaps one of the sweetest girls that the Prince had met, with him almost never turning down an opportunity to spend time with her. The two had become acquainted at a young age, with their parents often using the similarity of their names to tease them, saying that they would make a perfect pair. Despite their parents' lack of subtlety, the both of them got along quite well throughout the years, to the point that they had just recently been engaged to one another. Alex would never forget the smile on his father’s face when he had broken the news to him. He felt as if he had everything that he should ever want, his father’s approval, a loving fiancé, a strong relationship with members of the nobility… so why did that incessant itching insist on sticking around?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;After his proposal, Alice had been taking the opportunity to be particularly… eager when it came to her flirtations with Alex. That was probably only natural considering everything that was happening, but Alex couldn’t help but be uncomfortable with the whole affair. The way she would push her breasts into his flat chest and giggle, the way she would twirl her long hair and slightly squint her doe-like eyes suggestively, the way she would often attempt to explore… &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;further down&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;, all just made Alex feel completely sick to his stomach. Alex was a grown man at this point, well into his twenties, so it wasn’t as if he was naive to the idea of more sexual encounters between a man and a woman, nor did the idea itself disgust him or make him uncomfortable in any fashion. Just… whenever Alice would attempt to initiate, his throat would always twist until he said “I’m too tired, I’ve got a headache, I don’t know if we’re ready yet,” every excuse in the book he could find. He should have kept doing that, but when Alice again attempted intimacies, his fight or flight took control, resulting in him shouting at her to get away. The shocked and hurt look on her face had made him want to hide away for the rest of his days out of sheer guilt, but all his legs could do at the time was to run away, run until he was somewhere alone, somewhere he could get his thoughts straight, so here he was.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;What a coward he had been, to run away from his duties as a prince and husband, to run away from the promise that he had made to Alice when he had gotten down on one knee. What kind of man was he if he let nerves get the best of him while showing affection. Not just more intimate gestures, but even basic things like holding Alice close, or kissing her, or dancing with her made him feel nothing but bristles. Why was it that the simplest things imaginable held him back? The Prince picked up a small rock that he had found along his path, his frustration beginning to churn into a froth. A part of him wanted him to throw the rock in his hand with all his might, just to let it fly free and not think about the consequences, to prove that he could be strong. Such showmanship was common among the men that Alex was acquainted with, with many of them taking any opportunity to show off their strength. Thus, Alex would attempt to do the same. He wound up his arm, taking a fixed stance, and looked into the clearing before him. He prepared to let the rock fly, but the itching sensation began to take hold of his arm. The idea of throwing the rock just because he could… it felt wrong. His father would probably boast about cracking it in half, but to Alex… surely there were… &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;other&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; ways to prove he was strong. For now, he should probably head back and apologize to Alice. The Prince lightly discarded the rock with a soft, underhanded throw into the clearing before turning back towards the way he came.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“OW!” A shout of pain from within the forest alerted the Prince. He gulped, realizing that the source of the shriek just so &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;happened&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; to be in the direction that he had just thrown that rock. Surely that had to have been a coincidence, right? Despite such a solid and well thought out argument from his brain, he couldn’t in good conscience ignore the outburst, so he opted to make his way to the clearing where it had come from.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;As Alex slowly made his way into the clearing, it wasn’t long before he spotted a figure splayed out onto the floor. Despite the pained noises coming from her, Alex couldn’t help but stare at her for a moment. Her appearance was quite outlandish, with her dress being made up of bright colors and frills that were typically reserved more for royals and those of higher status. Despite that, he couldn’t help but admit that she wore it quite well, providing a delicate, feminine grace that came across even as she lay down on the floor. Her hair was long, and somehow was the shade of lilacs, while her body was petite, yet also secure. She truly looked so different than anyone else Alex had ever seen, but she somehow made it all look beautiful. He couldn’t seem to look away, a buzzing beginning to make itself known within his head. A strange, pointed hat lay beside her head that matched the color of her dress, with a single rock lying… next to… to her…&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Snapping out of his stupor, Alex rushed over to the woman. Unsure of how to approach this sort of thing, he lightly jostled her body in an attempt to get her attention. Thank goodness that she at the very least wasn’t bloody, that would have probably caused more panic from the both of them. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Um… are you alri-”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I’m wounded! I’m wounded!! I’m lucky I’m not dead! That rock might as well have been a bullet or a train for all the damage it did! Owwwwwwwww.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Alex had half a mind to back away slowly from the overly dramatic woman. Her propensity to make up words didn’t exactly provide much of a reason to trust her. As royalty, he was guaranteed one of the best educations in all of the land, so he felt as if he had the authority to say that the things this woman was saying such as “&lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;bullits&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;” and “&lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;tranes&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;” were more or less gibberish. While he had half a mind to declare the woman mad and move on with his life, he couldn’t help but feel bad for her current state. She looked to be legitimately in pain, there was no faking that, and considering that said pain was his fault, he certainly ought to at least see what he could do to help.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Is there anything I could do to be of assistance ma’am? I’m not exactly adept in medical matters, but if there’s anything I can do to make you feel better, I’m happy to provide it.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Just a hand will do please. I’m all out of whack at the moment, but once I’m back on my feet, I should be able to fix the bump on my head no problem.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The Prince hesitantly gave a hand to the fallen woman, who quickly got back up thanks to his stability.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Thank you so much! I feel much better now.” The woman dusted herself off, with the bump on her head suddenly having disappeared. “Ugh, the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;nerve&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; of some rocks, attacking people like they own the place.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Well… I might have influenced the rock to… ‘attack’ you.” Alex found it hard to look her in the eye after receiving such genuine appreciation. “I… I was just frustrated and I… I’m sorry. There isn’t an excuse for such poor care.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The woman laughed gleefully, as if I had just told her the funniest joke in the world. “Well of &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;course&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; you did! I mean, it’s pretty obvious. It’s written all over your face,” she said as she flicked Alex’s nose, causing him to flinch. “We all do silly things from time to time, trust me when I say I’m no stranger to being a dummy. What matters is that you decided to help out little ol’ me! Just be careful when you’re throwing rocks and stuff from now on. Those aren’t toys, y’know!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Alex couldn’t help but fully evaluate the figure that was in front of him, now that she wasn’t lying on the floor in “pain.” Despite the woman’s acceptance of his mistake, he felt the need to guard himself. As a prince, Alex was typically encouraged not to associate with more “eccentric” individuals, largely because those types were assumed to have the worst intentions. This woman’s behavior was admittedly a bit off-putting, but Alex couldn’t find any signs on her face of a negative resolve. If anything she was all smiles, said smile purer than anything Alex could conjure up. Hell, her face practically screamed towards his own that she was freer than any other creature within the world. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Must be nice,” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;a bitter part of him thought. He bit down on it before it could do any damage. “I mean… I couldn’t just leave someone who was… in clear agony I suppose?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Oh trust me, people have done much less with much more, so &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;think it’s only right if I reward you in some way. One second, please!” She snapped her fingers a few times, a piece of parchment and a quill, tip already dipped in ink, suddenly appearing in her hands.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Alex’s eyes widened, his mouth gaping. “H-How..?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Magic, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;obviously&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;. I keep forgetting how much of a lost art it is in some places. It’s a shame really.” She let out a sigh and began writing things down at a quick pace. “Regardless though, Alexander Capet, correct? Crown prince of the Royal family? I don’t know much about politics, but I assume that means you’re pretty important?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Said prince couldn’t help but flinch at the sudden use of his full name. “Just Alex please. Surely “Alexander” is too… formal at this current moment.” Admittedly, he was eager to find any excuse to not use his full name. It always just felt passive-aggressive whenever people would use it to refer to him, as if they were referring to someone else, someone better than he was.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The woman raised a thin eyebrow at the prince’s sudden correction, taking the opportunity to stare at Alex’s face. He couldn’t help but bristle at the sudden attention directed at him. What could possibly be so interesting about his face anyway? Alice would consistently mention how handsome his face was, but he just couldn’t see any of the good qualities that she would list. She’d talk about how strong and chiseled his face was, but to him it always looked &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;too&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; strong, to the point where he looked like a caricature. She’d talk about how attractive his facial hair was, but each hair on him always felt so unorganized. He would probably have shaved his beard off completely if Alice didn’t adore it so. At the very least, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;she&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; was happy with it, which helped make it somewhat bearable. Alex couldn’t help but feel a similar uncomfortable feeling as the woman stared into what felt like his very soul. She looked at him for what felt like for far too long before she gasped. “Oh my gosh! How did I not notice it before? That rock must have done more damage than I thought.” She took an opportunity to knock on her head a few times. “&lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Seriously&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Celia,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; how did you not notice such an obvious curse?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Alex stood at attention as “Celia” rambled to herself. “I… I’m sorry. Did you say a curse?” He really &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;really&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; hoped that he had just misheard her, but if he was being honest, it would just be &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;another&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; thing wrong with him to add to the pile. He was already messing up being a son, being a prince, being a good potential husband, why &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;not&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; add being literally cursed to the pile?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Perhaps his panic was a bit too obvious, because Celia immediately launched into damage control. “Oh nononono. It’s nothing to worry about. I mean, yes you &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;are&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; cursed, but still, nothing to worry about. It’s nothing that I haven’t seen and dealt with before. I’ve seen hundreds, if not thousands of people with the exact same curse. Seriously, I have no idea how a magic user could cast that many curses on such a large, random assortment of people from so many areas and eras. Only an absolutely sinister mastermind could weave that kind of magic. It’s strange that a lot of them were like you when I met them, not knowing that magic exists when they so &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;obviously&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; have been cursed, but I suppose that’s not my castle, not my princess.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“That is absolutely absurd! Someone would have noticed if I was ‘cursed.’ I have not experienced anything that warrants your concern.” Alex took a deep breath, attempting to gain back a bit of his composure. “Look, I apologize again about the rock. I really must be going now.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;As he turned to leave, the woman interrupted him. “You shouldn’t lie to a witch, y’know. I can see misery all over your face in huge, uneven blotches. It’s like you just made out with a bucket of paint.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Would you &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;please&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; stop talking nonsense? There is only so much of it that I can take.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;For the first time since Alex had seen her, Celia’s face became frustrated. “Fine! You want the straightforward approach? You look like absolute shit. You haven’t smiled in weeks, you’ve barely slept, and quite frankly, I’m not entirely sure if you’ve been living at all. As a concerned magical citizen, it’s my duty to help fix those things.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“How could you &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;possibly &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;say those things about me? You’ve known me for ten minutes &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;at most&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She looked at Alex with a slight smirk.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Right… it’s all over my face.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Precisely! Now, how shall we undo your curse? It’s pretty heavily ingrained into you, so I can’t just undo it. I’ll have to cast a counter-spell on you instead… but what kind is the question.” Celia tapped her quill against her head a few times, leaving a few noticeable ink marks on her cheek.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;It was clear that Alex had to stop this before it escalated further. “Look, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;look,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; I appreciate everything that you are trying to do for me, but meddling with this type of thing is not what I wish to do. My life is &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;fine&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; as it is. It’s normal. There is nothing wrong that needs to be fixed, I am not completely comfortable leaving this sort of thing in a complete stranger’s hands.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I… suppose that’s fair,” Celia said, a look of disappointment beginning to spread on her face. Before it could completely take over however, her smile reappeared. “How about this? I cast the spell, you experience what it has to offer, and then if you decide you don’t like it, I promise I’ll change everything back to how it was before, okay? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I…” That certainly seemed like a much safer offer, but surely there had to be some sort of catch to it?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Look, I just want to help you feel happy. I think it’s worth experimenting in case you find something you didn’t know you needed. Even royalty needs a change of pace sometimes.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Alex found it a bit hard to argue with that. He had been feeling uncertain about a great many things throughout the past few years, feeling as if he was stumbling around without a map. It might just be nice to potentially be pushed into the right direction. “I suppose you’re not completely wrong there. How do I know that you’ll hold up your end of the bargain?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Witches are magically obligated to complete any promises that they make. I’m pretty sure if I don’t keep my word, I’ll spontaneously combust!” Her quill glowed a brilliant pink, as if to emphasize that point.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Ignoring that slightly terrifying detail, Alex nervously stepped towards Celia. “I suppose I could give this a try… if it’ll truly help as much as you say it does.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Celia’s face could probably light a bonfire with how bright her smile was. “YES! You won’t regret this, Alex! An unchecked curse is serious business, so I’m glad you’re letting me take care of it. Now, I’ve already got the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;perfect&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; counter-spell for you!” She looked as if she was shaking from excitement as she held the piece of parchment out in front of her. “Basically, like I do with anyone who’s cursed, I’m going to cast a spell that will set everything as it’s supposed to be, undoing the curse. How the spell activates depends on what I think would be best for the person under said spell. For you, how about I have the spell set everything right as you experience true love!” Celia let out a pleasant sigh at the thought. “It’s a classic for a reason.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Alex mulled over the thought in his head. That definitely wasn’t a bad way to go about this. That type of magic was something he’d probably expect to hear as a child whenever his mother would read him a story. Things such as true love’s kiss and the like were still things that he occasionally thought about occasionally in the present, so why not potentially experience it? If anything, it would be a good way to potentially kindle even more love between himself and Alice. “I do happen to be currently engaged to a lovely woman, so I suppose that would be rather efficient.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“G-Great! I’m sure this’ll be super duper one hundred percent positively smooth for you then!” Alex couldn’t help but notice that Celia's smile looked slightly strained, but that was probably just a result of her current hyperactive state. “You just stand right there and let the magic happen. You’ll be feeling like a brand new you in no time.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Celia threw the parchment to the side, with the quill that had once been in her hand suddenly being replaced by a wand. She lightly pointed it at the Prince, waving it to and fro. The tip of the wand began to glow a bright pink. Alex’s nerves began to fray slightly, a part of him wondering if this had all just been an elaborate assassination plan. However, before he could worry any further, a beam of light that was the same bright pink as the wand had been shot out towards him. Despite the rather intense look of the spell, it felt somewhat pleasant. It felt as if Alex was being comforted by his parents, as if they and everyone else around him were telling him that it would be okay. He felt peaceful. Unfortunately, the feelings weren’t meant to last, as the beam eventually died out, and so too did the sensations.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Tadaaaa! Everything should be set for that nasty curse to be undone.” Celia took a moment to admire her handiwork before stepping back from Alex “I can’t wait to see the finished result, but I do have places to see and people to go, so I guess I’ll see you when the spell is complete. Byeeeeeeeee.” And with a single poof of smoke, it was as if Celia had never been in that clearing at all.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Alex’s head hurt slightly from that encounter. He honestly couldn’t help but doubt the idea that something would &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;actually&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; happen, but he supposed he would find out sooner than later. Perhaps he ought to go get a head start on undoing this “curse” by apologizing to Alice for his behavior.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div class="wi_authornotes"&gt; &lt;div&gt; &lt;div class="p-avatar-wrap"&gt;&lt;a class="avatar has-link" href="/profile/82590/eclaireo/"&gt;&lt;img id="acc_ava_change profile" alt="" src="https://cdn.scribblehub.com/avatar/s/20/ava_82590_1648731541.jpg"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="an_username"&gt;&lt;a href="/profile/82590/eclaireo/"&gt;Eclaireo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div style="clear: both;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="wi_authornotes_body"&gt;  Uhhhh hey! It's been a while since I last posted here. This is a story I've been working on for a while now, and I'm excited to finally start getting it out there. I've become pretty attached to the world and characters I've created here, and I'm hoping that you will too!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;You'll probably hear this a lot while I'm posting, but I really want to thank &lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/profile/154863/ternunfettered/?__cf_chl_tk=8ov_yTVQTIZsOqsP3sHKtpb3YRMY.KbApUkWZ9m8_OI-1718475593-0.0.1.1-8234"&gt;TernUnfettered&lt;/a&gt; for being an amazing test reader and for her constant ideas and support. She is not only an amazing writer herself (that you should definitely check out), but she's also a wonderful friend who has helped inspire me to get back into writing more. I genuinely cannot thank her enough for all of her help. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The current plan for this story is to gauge interest in regard to this opening chapter, and then once I've got a good backlog of chapters ready to be go, I'll start releasing them weekly. Hopefully that should be sooner than later, but I guess time will tell with that. At the very least, I can say that I'm excited to explore this world more and have a lot of cute stuff in store.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Thank you so much for reading. I hope you enjoyed it and have a lovely day! ^w^ &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
