      <title>Cracked Candy</title>
      <link>https://www.scribblehub.com/series/1120049/cracked-candy/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">91eb0b4b326724385f1a0349f77b632d552df4d7</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 14 Jun 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;This is a tragic oneshot, join Candy as she doesn't uncover who she is, or who her friend is.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I've had this oneshot in various drafts for years at this point. I originally wrote this as a challenge to myself: Can I write a story without referring to a character's name? It also let me prove that I can write an original setting. I've succeeded in both aspects and at this point I have 3.1k words I find compelling and would like to share them.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;Cracked&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;p&gt;“Candy!” A voice breaks me from my thoughts, which leave me, but only because the voice is much more important as I turn towards it, my eyes quickly move from the candle lit hall I am in with the crowds of people dancing towards a girl shorter than me, but with double my personality. In spite of myself a smile tugs at the corners of my mouth as I reply to her, the blonde curls on her head jumping up and down as she darts towards me, “Sshh, you shouldn’t call me that here.” I chide her half-seriously, my left hand gesturing at the party or whatever is going on around us.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Maybe I blinked too long or lost track of her movements but soon a lithe wall jumps onto me and I squeak, almost losing my footing, before my arms wrap around her, “I’ve missed you too, you know…” I say my eyes focusing on her warm brown eyes, like hot chocolate, before darting to the rest of her petite and rosy face, which captivates me a moment longer than necessary. “I can’t go on too long without my bestie~!” She joyfully retorts. I continue to study her face as if I am determined to carve it into my memory, odd considering how long I have known her, but my examination of her features doesn’t stop her lilting voice, “Come on, we’ve got so much to do now, and this ball is &lt;i&gt;boring&lt;/i&gt;. Have I got gravy on my face, why are you looking at me like that~?” She moves her hands from my body to her face, looking for an imperfection that isn’t there.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;As she does I separate myself from her, and take a look around, my eyes widen as I look at the elaborate palace I seem to be within, which is not what I expected. My eyes cast themselves downwards and I blink as I see myself in a ball gown which brings tears to my eyes, before I wipe them away quickly, no one can see them. Where &lt;i&gt;am &lt;/i&gt;I? Is the ball so boring I’ve forgotten &lt;i&gt;where &lt;/i&gt;it is? Do I &lt;i&gt;know &lt;/i&gt;anyone here? And, &lt;i&gt;Candy&lt;/i&gt;, what even is that na-&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;-And then I am dragged back to the moment by the ball of joy infront of me, a pouting ball of joy, “You’re just playing with me~! There’s nothing there~!” a smile once again tugs itself into existence on my face (smiling feels so odd). Anyway I might as well reply to her, “Well-,” I pause, her name escapes me, the awkwardness of the situation is soon forgotten as she takes charge of the conversation. “You think you’re funny don’t you~?” She half-giggles, “We have no time to talk anyway Candy~! We have so much to do tonight~!” She grabs my left hand: tight, and yanks it before pulling me out of the centre of the ballroom(?), off to its side (I am Candy?). As we move I marvel at my surroundings, entirely lit by chandelier and candle, with a great mosaic ceiling seemingly miles above my head, stained glass windows and stone pillars framing it all: How did I get invited to this… &lt;i&gt;fantasy&lt;/i&gt;? &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;When we stop it happens all too fast as I crash to the floor, headfirst, and a squealing girl lands on top of my back a “You okay?” escapes from my lips before I groan in pain myself. My groan deepens into a moan as the weight on my back shifts around before leaving me. I wait a bit, unsure if I should get up, before I hear giggling from behind me. I turn my head, as I still lie on my front, to the left where I can see a sitting figure with legs that are dancing up and down.“L-look at you~! Y-your dress,” her speech breaks into little bits as she descends into another fit, “A-are you o-okay with people s-seeing you like &lt;i&gt;that&lt;/i&gt;?” She then breaks off into another bout of giggling, panic grips my heart as I strain my head further to the left and see my bare legs and my dress’s skirt all over my middle. Red overtakes all other colours on my face as my hands dart down my body, trying to find the hem of my ball gown. I fail quickly as my fingers get lost in the dress’s luxurious fabric and instead stand up, one hand gripping the wall I landed a metre from and the other covering my behind, providing approximately no more decency than I had a moment beforehand. It takes awhile but I do get up and straighten my, now dirty, dress with help from my friend who managed, eventually, to stop laughing at my expense. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Candy~! We’re here~!” Looking up from my dirtied dress, I see a door and an eager bundle of joy next to it. One of my eyebrows rises in amusement that a door, and assumedly a room, is what so excites my smaller companion. And I stifle a giggle when my friend reverently opens the door, holding it open as I subconsciously take a step forward to take a look into whatever excited and continues to excite her so much.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;A bedroom, I am looking into a bedroom, I giggle at the unexpected twist and out of nerves as my feet make their way into the most extravagant bedroom my eyes have ever laid on. Painted in red and burgundy tinges the room is adorned in lovely pink flowers linked together by green thorns creating patterns, a rug sits at the base of a bed my eyes avoid out of what seems to be imagined embarrassment. Turning my eyes to the ceiling a curving pattern of wooden ridges seems to give support to the ceiling whilst remaining tantalising to the eye, almost certainly helped by the shadows cast from the chandelier central to the room. With only a few pieces of furniture, like the conspicuously large cupboard, and a door towards the back I, reluctantly, turn my eyes to the bed. Perhaps unexpectedly it isn’t a King size and instead a Queen size, but looking at the girl sitting on it, innocently swinging her legs and humming a familiar yet unknown tune to my ears, makes its smaller size a no-brainer. I feel my face heat up at that thought and drag my eyes to the actual bed and not its occupant, which is decorated in beautiful red and pink hues.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;A pair of coy eyes look over at me, now my own have stopped looking around the sliver of luxury I have landed in, the eye’s owner speaks, relieving me from a silence slowly growing awkward, “You finished looking around~? I Don’t know why you do that every time you’re here Candy,” she giggles and flutters her eyelashes, “Are you really that interested in &lt;i&gt;my&lt;/i&gt; room~?” She breaks off into laughter as it takes a few seconds for my brain to realise she’s just teasing (Candy feels &lt;i&gt;right&lt;/i&gt;).&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Despite my rationalisation my reply to her comes out just as you would expect, “A-ah n-no,” I nervously cough, “Wh-what did you want to show me..?” I say the first thing that comes into my mind and run with it as a distraction. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Apart from the room~? How about we do something to keep us occupied until the party ends?” As she speaks she opens up a bedside cabinet, and starts searching it,”Hopefully your parents forget you this time, it's been soo long since we had a sleepover~,” After awhile her endeavours pay off, “So I noticed you didn’t do your nails again, guess that's what we start with~.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;For an inexplicable reason my face once again regains heat upon hearing that, and my brain short circuits. My remaining thoughts circle around why having painted nails would cause this reaction, as my thoughts spiral and try to make sense of why such a benignly feminine action would cause this reaction the now determined bundle of joy next to me speaks up, “Sooo, what's your excuse~?” &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Well I, uh…”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Forgot again~?” The girl sits down next to me as she gives an excuse I readily take, nodding as a series of broken words come out of my mouth which, if her reaction is any guess (giggling), seems sufficient. “In that case this time I’ll give you one or two of these,” She clicks two bottles together.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Y-yeah maybe that’ll be a good idea,” The heat on my face from earlier has not yet gone and doesn’t seem like it will in the near future as she repositions us by grabbings my hands whilst continuing to talk, “Hmm I wonder what'd look good on you, the red would match your face, but that won't stay right~?” I think if my face could get hotter it would have with that comment, she continues with a drawn out, “Buuuttt, this purple would really compliment your dress.” She spends a bit of time mulling it over, her hands bringing various bottles up to her face which is seriously contemplating each hue under the rainbow. I try to keep up with the bottles in her hands but it all blurs together. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I am brought out of a stupor I didn’t know I was in by an affirmative “mhm~!” coming from my partner as she stands up, “Perfect, Candy what do you think about these~?” three bottles are dangled before my eyes, “We have this lovely blue,” she lifts the one on the left, a sparkly deep blue, “this glittering magenta,” again with the sparkles, “and this one - which I think will look best,” on the right is a blood red bottle - it doesn’t seem too impressive making me question why she thinks its the best - she cuts me out of my thoughts,” Stay here~! I need to get two more things~!” She darts off to a door in the corner of the room, presumably a bathroom, over her shoulder she calls out, “The red on your fingers, the blue on your toes~!”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Now, with my friend gone, I take a moment for myself… all of this has been so confusing, do I even know where I am? Who I am? My head hits the soft duvet of the bed as I think back, before the party, and am met with… nothing? No, not nothing, just greys and the occasional bright colour. All of it is blurry, but none of it feels as good, as &lt;i&gt;right&lt;/i&gt; as this party, even if some colours are similar in vibrance. Speaking of which, who am I friends with? I am… so familiar with her yet a name escapes me, I’ll have to ask sometime soon - I must have forgotten - and it’ll get awkward otherwise, especially when I meet her family or she meets mine; wherever they are.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;As my thoughts close, for once not interrupted, a door opens and I lazily lift my head up to see the bundle of joy dart towards me and take my hands, pulling me up to sit, I smile, and lean against her when she sits next to me as she wears an extremely endearing face of concentration as she looks at a bunch of bottles and cotton balls neatly arranged on a piece of paper sitting on her lap, whilst I am reluctant to no longer see that face I speak, “So? What do we have here?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“See~! I knew you forgot~!” and with that her head turns towards me with a face of playful indignation, “Well looks like I’ll &lt;i&gt;have&lt;/i&gt; to explain it to you again,”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;she pouts as she continues, “This time you are sooo taking a note with you.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I finish giggling at her retort and apologise. “Sorry, sorry! But, maybe I like forgetting if I can experience this each time we’re together.” I finish with a devilish grin which swiftly evaporates as a look of pain shoots through her, something which she tries to dissipate through a sharp shake of her head, as she replies somberly - an emotion I didn’t know she could produce, “I hope you haven’t been trying,” she sounds hurt.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I quickly nod, “S-sorry, I don’t actually want to forget, this has been the most fun I have had in… so long,” I have to try and rectify this.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She brightens up at my reply, “Good~!” and soon a wide smile covers her face, and a smaller one adorns itself onto mine, “So, fingers or toes first~?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;A sigh escapes me as it looks like my quick apology is enough to bring the radiance of her smile back as my friend takes my left hand. Not focusing too much, I assume she means to begin painting, instead both hands are taken - my cheeks flare up again - and I am pushed further onto the bed. When my companion begins giggling over my embarrassment my scarlet cheeks darken, before I start giggling myself.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;It takes a little bit for us to calm down, and even after a few minutes I still feel flushed and am torn: I don’t want to make a fool of myself, anymore than I already have, but desperately don’t want to abandon my friend. &lt;i&gt;Thankfully &lt;/i&gt;the decision is taken out of my hands as her fingers grasp my left one softly. My vision darts to her brown eyes and I feel red creeping further up my cheeks as I look at the focused face she is pulling: the tip of her tongue is escaping her mouth as she focuses on my left hand. Even the feeling of the refreshingly cool nail polish doesn’t convince me to move my eyes off her face.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;hr /&gt; &lt;p&gt;As she finishes off my last finger, it joins the rest of them in a deep red I  have quickly come to love. I let out a soft sigh of contentment at the gentle brushstrokes on my hand’s index finger, which quickly turns to a yawn. When I open my eyes after yawning I take in the sight of ten fingernails all beautifully red and ten glittering blue toenails below them, looking up to thank the painter I instinctively reach out and bring her close to me, in a hug… for some reason I blink tears from my eyes.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“T-thank you.” I get out before her arms wrap around me, when tears do come to me - soon afterwards - they feel unnatural.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Keeping my arms around her I pull back to get a look at the girl infront of me, “Are you okay?” My voice breaks a silence which had started following the end of the nail painting.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I should ask you that question, silly.” Even whilst fighting against tears her voice rings out rhythmically.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Why? You’re the one crying.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“You need this Candy, need me.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I pause at this, “Yes, you’re right bu-”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I bet you don’t remember my name again.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“-t… wha- you &lt;i&gt;know&lt;/i&gt;?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Lily, it’s Lily. Take a look around Candy.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I do as sh- Lily says, mentally taking her name down, and am confronted with the very same fairytale room as before. With its beautiful bed, high ceiling, panels and paterns… except this time it’s all grey. Only Lily is in colour. “W-what? Wher-” My distress is cut off as a yawn forces itself from my throat.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Because you’ll be gone soon.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“What do you mea-” My words are stolen by another yawn and a sudden headache.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“This,” Lily gestures around, “Is here - for me - but you don’t belong, it doesn’t think so.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Wh-where are we? Who doesn’t?” The headache deepens and &lt;i&gt;twists&lt;/i&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I’m still in our room, you aren’t - you’re going back to your…” She sighs, and one of her arms removes itself from me, “I can’t keep you with me forever.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“But…” I blink tears out my eyes, not from sadness, but from pain as my newly acquired migraine blurs my vision, if it wasn’t for Lily in front of me I’d be massaging my head.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“So, Candy, please… remember. For me, for you,” I open my mouth to speak, but she presses her finger to my mouth, “Take this… and remember.” &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“W-what, I-I don’t understand.” As I finish speaking I yawn, and lean on Lily more, my strength long gone.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“You don’t need to yet, I don’t fully know, just take this.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“B-but what is it?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Secret~” Some of Lily’s childish nature re-enters her voice as she presses something glass into my hand, “Don’t lose it.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“W-,” I lose my voice for a second, moving my jaw has become a noticeably hard thing to do, “When will I see you again..?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“As soon as you feel like it, Candy I… I’m sorry” Lily removes her other arm from me and I feel her melt into the grey room… thankfully I don’t see that.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I am left alone. Which feels normal… but &lt;i&gt;wrong&lt;/i&gt; (of course it does).&lt;/p&gt; &lt;hr /&gt; &lt;p&gt;I wake up from an oddly calming, nice, sleep. I don’t even need to look outside to see it is still dark, the lack of sunlight coming from the bathroom is enough. The shadeless light above me remains, as ever, off. Turning to my side, grunting at my concrete-like bed, the bare wall looks back at me. I don’t know why I thought I’d see anything other than the normal.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;With another grunt I land onto the floor, which immediately lets out a sound of protest, it's dark… I should sleep some more, it's the healthy thing to do, but I don’t… I feel off, wrong, so I stumble towards the bathroom, despite it being a few feet from my bed the journey feels odd, like I’ve forgotten the layout of my room. In the bathroom I drop something on the floor, I don’t know what I was holding, as I slap my face with some water and look into my mirror - despite its cracks the same face looks back at me, nothing new, same everything. Nothing is different, yet I still feel like a poorly made puppet.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;A deep sigh escapes my throat as I turn to leave the bathroom, planning to get a few sleepless hours in before the sun rises, and I slip. My head meets the wall a few times before I stop myself in a half crouch, my arms leaning on the wall, my eyes facing the floor focus on a bottle, small, and full of a beautiful &lt;i&gt;red&lt;/i&gt;… Where its label should be (why do I know it &lt;i&gt;should &lt;/i&gt;have a label?) is a lavender paper with two simple words written in beautiful cursive: ‘for Candy’.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Water hits the bottle and my hand reaches for my face… feeling tears. My legs buckle, and I slide down the wall, tears flood my face but my eyes remain glued to the two words on a simple bottle of nail polish in front of me. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;My heart &lt;i&gt;aches &lt;/i&gt;and blackness begins to cover my vision. But before I succumb to it my deep, broken, voice breaks a cold silence and says: “Lily”.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div class="wi_authornotes"&gt; &lt;div&gt; &lt;div class="p-avatar-wrap"&gt;&lt;a class="avatar has-link" href="/profile/17110/rikki_rattus/"&gt;&lt;img id="acc_ava_change profile" alt="" src="https://cdn.scribblehub.com/avatar/s/4/ava_17110_1718399149.jpg"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="an_username"&gt;&lt;a href="/profile/17110/rikki_rattus/"&gt;Rikki_Rattus&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div style="clear: both;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="wi_authornotes_body"&gt;  Thank you for reading!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I don't want to get anyone's hopes up, I've had this chapter in some form for a long time and have never had a concrete idea or plan to continue the story past this point. If you're inspired by this in any way feel free to write your own Cracked Candy.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
