      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Catarina has a huge crush on her coworker, Milla. The fact that they co-work as vtubers for the same agency slightly complicates the situation, but Cat has a plan to get closer to her crush and just enough hope to believe it will all work out.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;When Milla's coworker suggests they do some stream collaborations in-person, she's terrified. No one knows what she looks like or that she's trans, and if the way Catarina has been teasing her is any indication, nothing good will happen if she finds out. She has no way of knowing what kind of cruel plans Catarina has in store for her, and she doesn't want to find out.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;What does it mean if I want to kiss you? is an 18k word lesbian romance with awkward flirting, heartfelt confessions of love, and a meddling little sister.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;Chapter 1&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration:underline"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Milla&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;em&gt;Catarinyan&lt;/em&gt;:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; Hey, cutie. You’re in Seattle too, right? Want to plan a LAN collab with me ? Could be a lot of fun. I’m thinking a week’s worth of sleepovers and streams. How does next week work for you?  :)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I stared at the message on my screen, my cursor blinking in the reply box in time to my stuttering thoughts. Why would we do an in person vtuber collaboration? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;After a moment of thought I could see the logic.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;It was infinitely easier to do stream collaborations virtually, especially for vtubers given the avatars, but there was a certain atmosphere that came with two people being in the same room that couldn’t be replicated online. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Unfortunately for me, it was doubtful that atmosphere would be pleasant, especially with Catarina. I was a disaster socially, and Cat was intimidating at best and threatening at worst. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Every time we did streams together she’d tease me mercilessly with flirty comments and innuendos. It didn’t help that my avatar was a tiny snake-girl and that my motion capture software somehow managed to detect me blushing and displayed it on my model.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Admittedly, I didn’t have a good reason to ask her to stop; our chats ate it up, and I desperately needed the money. And it wasn’t like I hated it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;It also might’ve been my fault in the first place…&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;When I sent my application into the vtuber organization, I’d missed the line of text that explained that you were supposed to already have a persona/character crafted and your application video was supposed to be in character. So, like a complete doofus, I submitted a video of me acting like myself.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Imagine my confusion when I got a call back and they told me they loved my shy cutesy persona, and that my character wouldn’t need to be changed much for my debut. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;In the few months since I’d started, I’d been struggling to find my character, given my main feedback was ‘keep doing what you’re doing’, which has been being myself, but I had no clue who I was. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span