t:400"&gt; I pitched it to the bosses by myself because you were taking too long to respond and I got a double thumbs up, so let's do this! I’d love to have you (over) ;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Shoot. Saying no to her was one thing, but the bosses were another. They were scary, which was great when you were getting harassed online and needed them to back you up, but terrible when you missed your stream quota and they sent you a sternly worded email. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;This is exactly what I meant about her being mean to me. She’d do something intimidating like threatening me with our bosses and then follow it up with a teasing remark and a smiley face. I was suspicious of the invitation before, but now, with her scheming to get our bosses involved, I was sure she had plans to take pictures of me and blackmail me with them or something equally devious.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I let out a groan and leaned forwards to let my forehead rest on my desk. Maybe if I wore the classic oversized hoodie, she wouldn't notice how gross my body was? And I’d have to never use my voice… Could I do streams without speaking?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;This was going to be a horrible disaster.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration:underline"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Catarina&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;This was going to be amazing. I hummed as I went through my grocery shopping, thinking of what I could cook for Milla when she stayed over. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Crushing on a coworker, especially one I hadn’t actually met, was a terrible idea, but I couldn’t help it. She, or her character at least, was so &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;cute&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; it was impossible to restrain my growing infatuation. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I knew even if I wasn’t on stream teasing her over voice call, I’d be doing the same in the chat as one of her fans. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;And I knew that because that’s what I did. I was, on an alternate account, one of her biggest donors, and it was worth every dollar to hear her read my teasing comments and blush.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I was worried about how much of it was an act, however. It wasn’t like people in real life blushed &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;that &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;often, and could the software even detect blushing? Or was she just pushing a button to make her avatar blush?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Ugh, I would just have to plan for the worst and hope for the best. I really couldn’t know how similar she was to her character until we interacted out of character, and so far, she was really hard to pin down outside of streams, and when she actually answered my messages, she did so in character. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;So I couldn’t know if she was acting like herself, what she looked like, or if she was gay… But I still had hope. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I grabbed a bag of chocolate chips off the shelf and threw them into my cart; girls like homemade cookies right? Shit, I should ask her if she has any food allergies.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I opened up my messages and I couldn’t stop my heart from jumping when I saw she’d finally messaged me back.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;em&gt;LaMia&lt;/em&gt;:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;heya Cat, next week works for me, i forgot to make a stream plan for 27th-31st because i thought it was next month already, so you’re kinda saving me from doing more planning work, and we can just say it was my secret plan all along. Ramble over\&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I smiled reading her message and my brain couldn’t help thinking how much unnecessary work it would be to act like a dork in my dms if she wasn’t this dorky in real life. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;em&gt;Catarinyan&lt;/em&gt;:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Lovely. I want you as soon as possible. Do you have any food allergies or dietary restrictions? I’ll be wooing you with my cooking for a few days, and I’m doing my shopping now. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Logically, it was a terrible idea to flirt with her, but I had a foolproof excuse prepared to justify it (to myself): if she’s going to message me in-character, I should message back in-character. My character was flirty and teasing with her all the time, so it only made sense for me to do it more in dms. It wasn’t my fault. Oh, she messaged me back.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;em&gt;LaMia&lt;/em&gt;: &lt;/b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;no meet&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;My heart dropped and I stopped in the middle of the aisle to hunch over, staring at my phone, much to the ire of the person walking behind me. She didn’t want to meet me? Had I been too forward? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;em&gt;LaMia&lt;/em&gt;: &lt;/b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;*meat&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Oh. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Everything was fine. My lips tugged upward into a grin and my leather boots squeaked against the tiles as I skipped down the aisle. I continued with my shopping, picking up some tofu I had no idea how to cook, and pointedly ignoring the fact that Milla had such a strong influence on my mood despite having never met her. It was just a harmless crush, what could go wrong?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
