    <item>
      <title>Of Fluff and Garbage</title>
      <link>https://www.scribblehub.com/series/1104103/of-fluff-and-garbage/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">26f4a365784cfd8e4ae7c7567bcf2fc0c022edc0</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jul 2024 11:18:07 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;A freak tornado struck a small town, and now a strange fog is hanging in the air. It's dark and glistening, and it feels dangerous. Nevertheless, relief workers and volunteers are working tirelessly to save as many people as they can. I'm sure it's fine. None of them are going to get sick, none of them are going to experience any kind of revelations about themselves, and absolutely none of them are going to be sprouting any tails, right?&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This story is set in the Hare Apparent Storyverse created by Sylkweaver. It was written with the hopes of being able to stand on its own, but knowledge of Hare Apparent and of Arknights can certainly add something to the experience. It follows Provence and Scavenger, my two favorite Arknights lesbians, as they find each other again on Earth. I hope you enjoy!&lt;br /&gt; Also, huge thanks again to Sylkweaver! Syl is amazing and helped a lot to get this story off the ground. She answered every question I had and proofread every chapter, and I think that's cool of her. Go read Hare Apparent! It's worth your time!&lt;br /&gt; Cover art by my lovely partner Lynn, go show them some love at twitch.tv/stumblynn cuz they deserve it.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;FG-1: !!Emergency!!&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;p&gt;I woke up to something hitting me in the face.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ordinarily, this would be cause for some concern, but by this point I’d gotten used to it. My roommate, Hailey, had decided the most efficient way to wake me up was a sudden pillow to the head. As a result, any time there was some emergency, or anything that required my immediate attention, she’d go to the living room, grab a pillow off the couch, and fling it my way.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;All this is to say, my reaction to the sudden assault was far from unusual.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“G’morning Hailey.” I half mumbled as I dragged myself up into a sitting position.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“MLR called. They want us by nine, fully kitted out.” She was standing in my bedroom doorway, already dressed in her usual cargo pants, muscle tank, and beanie. “It sounded urgent.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;That got my attention. There had been nothing in the forecast these last few days to indicate there was any risk of inclement weather, but if MLR was reaching out on such short notice, clearly something had happened anyway.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Know what it’s about?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Something happened up north. Government response seems inadequate. Eric wants us to step in.” She turned to leave as I rose from the bed. “There’s food on the table. Don’t take too long in the shower. Lemme know when you’re ready, Dan.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I smiled a bit as I plodded over to the bathroom to begin my morning ritual. Hailey was always a bit gruff, but if you took the time to get to know her, it was pretty obvious she was much more compassionate than she let on. Given her history and the circumstances in which we’d met, her attitude was certainly understandable.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The short woman had been curled up in an alley, her white hair matted, her skin caked with grime. There was a bullet hole in her shoulder. I tried to call an ambulance, but she begged me not to. I figured she’d been caught up in something that could’ve gotten her into trouble.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Plenty of folks would’ve called anyway. Plenty more would’ve called the cops as well. I just grabbed a first aid kit from my car, and did what I could. She was damn lucky I worked for MLR, a non-profit committed to disaster relief, and that we required all our front line relief workers to be trained in first aid. If she’d taken a turn for the worse, or if the injury was infected, I’d probably have taken her to a hospital anyway, but she got lucky, and in the end, she moved in with me, getting a job with the MLR on my recommendation.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;It was a good thing, too. As new pockets of originium began appearing around the world, as cases of oripathy, the disease originium caused, continued to spike, and as natural disasters seemed to occur more and more frequently, we needed all the hands we could get. She passed through all our training with flying colors and started working alongside me within a few weeks.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;These thoughts kept my mind occupied as I brushed my teeth then hopped in the shower, skipping through most of my normally extensive hair care routine. I dried off as quick as I could and threw my brown hair into a messy braid once I got dressed. Some guys might think it’s weird that I put so much effort into my hair, or that I preferred to keep it long, but I took pride in it as my own form of self expression. Something that set me apart.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Now looking at least somewhat presentable, I hustled out into the living room, put on my boots, and grabbed my backpack. True to her word, Hailey had left an orange, a protein bar, and a travel mug of coffee on the table, and I scooped them all up before stepping outside to meet her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“You ready?” She was waiting by my truck, tapping her foot impatiently.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Yep.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I pulled out my keys, and Hailey snatched them from my hand before I could react.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“You eat. I’ll drive.” With that, she hopped into the driver’s seat, leaving me no time or chance to argue, and I found myself smiling again. Whatever work we had today, I knew we could face it together.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The drive itself was quiet, interrupted only by the crunch of the protein bar and the hum of the engine. It wasn’t a long drive, and by the time I polished off the last bite of orange we were pulling into the MLR building’s parking lot. The building wasn’t exactly huge, but it didn’t need to be. We rarely met in person, and the money saved was part of the reason MLR could afford to keep us as employees rather than volunteers. As much as I loved being able to help people, I did need to eat, after all.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The exterior was squat, brown, and unassuming, and today it was surrounded by more cars than I’d ever seen. Whatever happened, it looked like it was all hands on deck, and I found myself wishing I’d thought to check the news on the way here. In any case, Hailey and I hurried inside. I tossed a quick wave to Becca at the front desk before heading to the common area, the only room in the building that could accommodate this many people.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;We’d arrived only a few minutes before nine, and the meeting started almost immediately. Eric, MLR’s founder, placed himself in the common room’s center as he addressed the gathered crowd.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Thank you all for coming on such short notice.” The murmurs that had filled the air died down at once as he began to speak. “As some of you may know, early this morning, an unexpected storm struck Michigan’s upper peninsula. That storm spawned not one, but two separate F5 tornados… I’d like to reiterate, Michigan’s rural communities were struck by two separate F5 tornadoes. The last F5 on record occurred in 2013. The last one to hit Michigan was back in 1956. These people are going to need all the help they can get, and we’re going to give it to them.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Well damn. That explained the rush.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;After that, he started giving out assignments. We’d split into small teams, each assigned  an area to work in, allowing us to cover a wide area while prioritizing those that suffered the most damage.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“And lastly, Hailey, Daniel, Michael, and Jess, you’ll be coming with me to Bakkerville. It was near the center of the storm, and one of the twisters carved a path straight through it. They’ll need our help more than anywhere else.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I nodded, letting steadfast determination wash over me. The MLR had the power to help people, &lt;i&gt;I &lt;/i&gt;had the power to help people, and to me, that’s what made this job worth doing. I turned to Hailey, expecting to see the same resolve in her eyes, but she just looked worried, more than I’d ever seen from her before. Then she noticed me looking and grinned, but it felt forced. She hardly ever smiled, after all.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I could worry about that later. RIght now, I needed to get to the trucks. Every minute counted, and we needed to get on the road as soon as possible. As I joined the others en route to the garage (a structure much larger than the MLR building itself), leaving Hailey to double check our bags, Michael sidled up next to me.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I didn’t like Michael very much. He was committed to his work, and he was damn good at it, but he was rude and abrasive, deliberately so. I often found myself wondering what could’ve possibly compelled him to get into this line of work.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Hey Danny!” He punched me lightly in the shoulder. “Looks like you’re stuck with Hailey again. Tough luck, buddy.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Case in point.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I’m not stuck with her. She’s my coworker and my friend, and she’s damn good at her job.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I tried to ignore him after that, walking purposefully towards the massive truck I’d grabbed the keys for. Unfortunately, he either didn’t notice, or didn’t care.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Ohhhhh, right. You live with her, don’t you? That’s why she always follows you around, isn’t it? Why she’d bite the head off basically anyone else. You two probably ba-”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“You’re either gonna shut up and grab our truck, or I’m reporting you for sexual harassment. Your call.” Jess, the hero of the hour, had appeared quite suddenly behind us, and she did not look happy. She was only a step below Eric in the MLR hierarchy, and we all knew it. Michael didn’t respond, instead sheepishly grabbing the keys she offered him and scampering off.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I can still report him if you want. His behavior was unacceptable, and both you and Hailey deserve better.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I think I’m good. For now, at least. Sounds like we need all hands on deck for this one, and unfortunately, Mike’s hands are pretty useful.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Alright then.” She gave me a quick smile before turning away. “I’ll make sure he stays outta your hair. Now let’s get moving.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;After that, it was only a matter of moments before we piled into our two trucks, heavily laden with food, bottled water, blankets, and everything else we could need, and drove off. We had a job to do, and if we failed, people were going to get hurt.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I didn’t realize it at the time, but this would be the last taste of normalcy I’d have for a long time.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div class="wi_authornotes"&gt; &lt;div&gt; &lt;div class="p-avatar-wrap"&gt;&lt;a class="avatar has-link" href="/profile/54812/ashlynflagg/"&gt;&lt;img id="acc_ava_change profile" alt="" src="https://cdn.scribblehub.com/avatar/s/13/ava_54812_1621642868.jpg"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="an_username"&gt;&lt;a href="/profile/54812/ashlynflagg/"&gt;ashlynflagg&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div style="clear: both;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="wi_authornotes_body"&gt; We're so back! Welcome to my first attempt at fanfic! This story is based off of my two favorite lesbians from the mobile game Arknights, as well as the story that convinced me to try Arknights, Hare Apparent by Sylkweaver. It's set in the same universe as Hare Apparent and was made with input and assistance from Syl, so please go check out that story if you haven't already. It's really good, and she's planning more stories in that universe as well!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I've tried to make this story fairly understandable to those who haven't read Hare Apparent or played Arknights though. Let me know how well I did, and if you have any questions about the lore or world building, feel free to ask! Anyways... enjoy!!!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
