    <item>
      <title>My Crossdressing Friend Keeps Wanting My Attention!</title>
      <link>https://www.scribblehub.com/series/1113591/my-crossdressing-friend-keeps-wanting-my-attention/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">d0d3402cd42087d49e5694fbe4f73830d5b3c968</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 29 Jun 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;[SERIES IS ON AN INDEFINITE HIATUS]&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Takeshi has everything all planned out! He's going to be a grade-A student for his final year of junior high, with excellent marks all around! Just one step out of many to eventually become a highly respected and valued member of society as an adult!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Now if only his friend Hikaru could take his education as seriously. Goofing off, joking around, the occasional prank, he had a habit of distracting people with some random antic. Now he's gone so far as to crossdress at school! One can only hope he'll stop messing around eventually, but that's just Hikaru for you. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Though admittedly, the uniform does suit him. Sometimes, between his looks and the way he's starting to act, it's easy to forget Hikaru's even supposed to be a boy at all.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;But... that's unimportant. Don't let him get in the way of what matters. He's just trying to draw some attention, like he always does. Yes, that's all there is to it. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;...Right?&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;Chapter 1 – Hikaru Wants to Crossdress&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Spring. A time of beginnings and ends. To mark the start of something new, a bright and hopeful future.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;It’s difficult to deny the inherent romanticism that often came with the cherry blossoms falling to the ground. I tried to remain calm and expressionless on my walk to school, but it’s hard to resist putting a small smirk on my face.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I felt confident, self assured. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Six years of elementary, two years of junior high. Just one more, and I’ll have completed another step in my life’s journey. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I had a plan set out for my life. My grades in junior high have been excellent so far, making me a model student. I’ll achieve just as great if not better results this year, and I’ll apply for a respected high school that I’ve already picked out! There, I will continue to excel, perhaps even join the student council! I’ll find a passion for myself, then choose the appropriate university to best fit my goals. Perhaps I’d even study abroad at one of those foreign schools, like Oxford. Either way, with my life on a continuous upwards momentum, I will then eventually become a highly respected member of adult society!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Just one more year and I, Takeshi Muramoto, will move closer to achieving my ambitions!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I stood in front of the school building, pausing just to look at the sight. It was glorious. I was ready to meet the remainder of my junior high education with the utmost seriousness and dedication! Study hard for every test! Aim for a score of 90 at the absolute minimum! Become top of the class! &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Yes, my third and final year begins now-!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Suddenly I felt an arm jump down to drape on my shoulder, a familiar voice ringing in my ear. “Good morning, Takeshi! Ready for another year?!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I grunted, “Could you please let go, Hi-?” Though I stopped when my head turned to look at them, and I saw who I was talking to.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I could swear that had been the voice of my friend Hikaru, but this was someone with much longer hair. As they let go and I took a step back, I then noticed their uniform. It was a girl. “M-My apologies, I thought you were…?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I paused, pushing up my glasses. It was an odd feeling, because now that I looked at their face again, it really did…&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;No, it couldn’t be.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The girl(?)’s curious but innocent expression then morphed into a familiar mischievous grin. Before I could even react, she busted out laughing, holding her stomach with her hands. “Oh man, I got you good! Pfft-! Ahahaha!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I was frozen, my mind taking a moment to process what was now obvious. “H-Hikaru?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“You totally thought some girl was hitting on you! Oh my god, that’s so hilarious!” She- no, *he* continued! The uniform admittedly fit him well. Even knowing who he was, I was almost mixing up his gender in my head.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Yes, while the person in front of me definitely looked like a female classmate, he was in fact a boy. My friend, Hikaru Nishiki.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“How-?! Why-?!” I sputtered out. I didn’t even know what to ask first. “Why on earth are you wearing a girl’s uniform?!” I finally asked. “And is… that a wig?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Yep!” Hikaru delicately brushed the locks to the front of his face. “Super smooth too! Wanna feel?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Don’t just ignore the main question!” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Oops, sorry, silly me. Totally forgot that a guy like you would *neeever* dare lay your hands on a pure maiden.” He dramatically flipped his hair back, then feigned a shy embarrassment by laying a hand on his cheek. “I was too forward with you, forgive my rudeness.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I grunted, covering my hand with my face for a moment. Just of course Hikaru’s antics would pop up on the first day back. Though admittedly, dressing up like this felt like a step up. “Could you quit screwing around? I need to go find out what class I’m in, and you should too, after you change back to your normal uniform.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Mmm, no.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“No, what?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I’m not changing back.” He explained, lifting his lips up into an exaggeratedly smug smirk.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“...Why?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Uhhh, cuz it’s funny, duh.” Hikaru raised an eyebrow, looking at me like I had just asked something silly.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“You’re going to dress like that in front of the whole school?” I asked.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Not much point in going through with this joke otherwise.” Hikaru crossed his arms. “Gotta go all in, you know?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“So you admit that this is an elaborate joke?” Knowing Hikaru, it didn’t take a detective to figure that out, though at least he was acknowledging it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Gah!” He practically jumped, leaning back and holding his hands together in front of his chest, like some scared frail schoolgirl. “How cruel! You think my poor maidenly heart is but a sick joke? How could you be so mean, Takeshi?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I sighed once more. I’d entertained Hikaru’s antics enough. “I’m going to go find the class roster for this year.” I began walking as I said this, although Hikaru was quick to perk his eyes and follow behind.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Jeez, you’re no fun. Not even gonna blush at the thought of your best friend showing up all cute in a girl’s uniform?” He wistfully sighed, “And here I thought it fit me so well.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;It did, loathe as I was to admit. But I wouldn’t ever say that out loud. I was not going to encourage him. “Where did you even get that? The uniform, I mean.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“It’s my big sis’ old one, found it in her room. She’s off to university, so she won’t notice or miss it.” Hikaru casually explained.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I suppose if there’s someone you could borrow clothes from, it’d be your sibling. She was likely the same size when she was at our age. “Even so, you’re still breaking the dress code.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Nah, just has to be *one of* the uniforms.” He threw his hands behind his head. “They changed it a few years back. Think cuz of some progressive gender stuff and making people more comfortable. Something like that.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Ah, that was true. The world was becoming a different place slowly, moving on to accept the different ways people expressed themselves. But still, that didn’t excuse Hikaru abusing those ideas to play a stupid ‘prank.’ Although it was relatively harmless, so there was little point in arguing about it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Ah, the class rosters!” Hikaru leapt ahead of me to peek at them. I, of course, walked calmly. While Hikaru rudely bumped into a couple of students as he made his way there, I slipped past them. He didn’t have to be so careless as to his surroundings, one of those things that separated us, I suppose.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;When I started scanning the roster however, it only took a short moment for Hikaru to announce his placement out loud. “Oh, I’m in class C!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;My eyes drifted towards class C, sure enough, Hikaru Nishiki was listed right there. Though as I scanned the rest of the class…&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Oh, and you too! We’re in the same class again!” Hikaru proclaimed. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Yep, right there. Takeshi Muramoto. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Obviously I should have been satisfied with this outcome. Hikaru was my friend after all. Even if he had a habit of messing around, he was one of the few people who actually talked to me between classes. I always suspected the others found me intimidating. After two years in the same class together, go figure we’d go for three in a row.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Even so, I couldn’t help but feel a sense of foreboding for this year in particular…&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;hr /&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Morning everyone!” Hikaru greeted ahead of me as he walked in through the class door. He held a reserved hand up in front of his neck while the other waved, which I had to assume was an intentional gesture to appear more girly and feminine. He really was going through with this whole joke, huh.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The classroom was sporadic at the moment, various students scattered about, chatting to whichever friends they were lucky to be assigned with this year. Heads naturally turned at Hikaru’s entrance, and I could swear one guy looked starry eyed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Wha-?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Whoa, is that a new girl?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;It wasn’t hard to hear what words were being said among the scattered chattering.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Wait, Nishiki?” One girl asked, sitting on her desk. I believe she was in our class last year too.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Yep, it’s me!” He proclaimed. “I… I actually have something to tell you all!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Okay, hold on, no, where was this bit going?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“You see, for ages, my family line has suffered from a curse…! That their second-born daughter will not live to see adulthood!” Hikaru created a grieving expression on their face, as if telling the sad story of a dead loved one. “So when I was born, my parents chose to raise me as a boy.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;He clasped his hands to his chest, “But no more! I refuse to live a lie any longer! I want to be honest with you all, my dear classmates, and-!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;At this point, I bumped my shoulder with him to stop his overdramatic speech. “He’s just crossdressing today.” I briefly explained.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;To which one of the male classmates mouthed an ‘ah.’ “Yeah, sounds like something Nishiki would do.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Most of the class proceeded to murmur amongst themselves in agreement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;They were just casually accepting and going along with it?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Hikaru stuck a bit of his tongue out to everyone and bonked a hand on his head like some goofy anime schoolgirl. “Whoops, guess ya got me!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“You really almost had me fooled, you know.” That female classmate from earlier added. “The uniform fits you so well too, did you have it fit?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Aw, thanks!” He did a little spin. “No, it’s just the old one my sis used!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;A male classmate nearby balled his fist and grit his teeth, as if channelling all of his emotions. “The first day of the semester, and my class has an otokonoko…! Life is finally complete!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;What?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Hikaru let out a mock giggle.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Was everyone else just rolling along with it?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Was I the odd one out here?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Oh, and would you look at that!” Hikaru rushed over to a spot in the middle of the class, where he lay a hand on two empty seats right next to each other. “Looks like we happen to have neighbouring seats! Come on, Takeshi!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“R-Right.” Unable to find any other words to respond with, I simply nodded and took my seat. All the while, Hikaru smiled sweetly and invitingly at me. It almost made me uncomfortable, how easy it could be to mistake him for an actual girl. Even when he wasn’t exaggerating his mannerisms or anything, he was practically unassuming.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I sat down, and Hikaru then plopped down himself. I glanced to my side, and I saw him kicking his legs under the desk. What was he being so happy about? No, he’s just messing around, sticking with the dumb crossdressing bit. He even held both his hands on his cheeks as he leaned forward on his desk. He was definitely trying to act extra girly.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I’ll give you this, I don’t think whatever you’ll do for the rest of the year will beat this.” I noted. “I don’t think anyone’s gonna forget you wearing a girl’s uniform on the first day of the year.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Hm?” Hikaru seemed caught off guard by that comment, for some reason. As if I had pointed out something that he hadn’t even considered. He looked up at the ceiling, and started thinking. “Actually, I think I might keep it going.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“What?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;He turned his head back to look at me. “Maybe I’ll do it tomorrow too, and the day after.” He grinned, “Hey, I might just decide to be a girl for the whole year! Now *that*’d be funny!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;It was obvious he was deriving some form of joy from that idea. How? Probably because it was, indeed, funny to him somehow. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;But I wasn’t sure how to feel, I felt… weird.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;There was a weird pit in my stomach, thinking about that prospect. Was it because I wanted to focus all my efforts on my education this year, while Hikaru was goofing off about some elaborate joke he wanted to do? Or was it because of that weird feeling I got earlier, when we were about to sit down?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;…&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;No, don’t be stupid. I was just getting second hand embarrassment from how little my friend took his education seriously. This was just like every other time he’d mess around. I just worried for his future, in some way. The type of adults who become respected members of society didn’t spend their school years crossdressing and goofing off. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;There was nothing more to it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;This was the start of my new daily life, with my crossdressing friend, and her distracting antics.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;…His, I meant his.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;div class="wi_authornotes"&gt; &lt;div&gt; &lt;div class="p-avatar-wrap"&gt;&lt;a class="avatar has-link" href="/profile/154863/ternunfettered/"&gt;&lt;img id="acc_ava_change profile" alt="" src="https://cdn.scribblehub.com/avatar/s/38/ava_154863_1712054303.jpg"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="an_username"&gt;&lt;a href="/profile/154863/ternunfettered/"&gt;TernUnfettered&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div style="clear: both;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="wi_authornotes_body"&gt;  Fair warning, this is gonna be a bit different than my other story. The chapters are gonna be shorter, and I want to keep a more lighthearted tone. Still, I hope you enjoy and look forward to more!&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
