      <title>Merry Gentlemen</title>
      <link>https://www.scribblehub.com/series/1110392/merry-gentlemen/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">e8ec5664a79e2dba2a3f9636a6af45faceac04ce</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 05 Jun 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;For years the land has been frozen in an eternal winter and Noel, the prophesized savior, must choose between two options. Staying at the Estate with Merry Byers who drains his gift or finding Snow; the one who cursed the land. Will Noel be able to resolve his internal conflict with Snow in time to break the curse?&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;Prologue&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Wishful Greetings,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;To whom this letter is addressed, a joyous tiding is here for thee. On the longest night of the year, the Evening Star will bestow a gift unto thee. Once the sun has set, the Ceremony of Blessing will be held at the Holly Cathedral.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Enclosed within this letter is a list of requirements that must be completed before the Ceremony of Blessings. The train ticket provided will accommodate thee from the nearest train station to the Festive Inn residing in Yuleville. Further instructions await thee in thy chamber at the Festive Inn. Anyone who fails to arrive in a timely manner will overturn thy right to the gift.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Until then, rejoice and may good fortune find thee.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Festive Cheers,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Head Merrys&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For centuries, boys all over the countryside would wake up with a similar letter placed at the foot of their front door. Each one would rip the letter open to see a message written in green ink. Shouting to their parents, they would flee in an instant to hear what the letter said to them. Smiles adorned the parents’ faces as the boys would hear this joyous tiding of a bright future awaiting them. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;While this was a call for celebration, the families took haste in preparing their sons for this blessing. Each boy would arrive in Yuleville with a sense of awe as festivities reigned over the days leading to the ceremony. The Festival of Winter Solstice entertained them on the main street while the time of Dedication showed them devotion. After those twenty days, it was finally time for the boys to receive their blessing. The Ceremony of Blessing would commence, and a gift would be bestowed upon them one by one. Each gift would grow in the wellness of all good and evil to balance the holiday spirit for all the world. The gift would thrive within these gentlemen for the length of a thousand years. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Yet over the centuries, they drifted away from their true purpose. Less of them would receive these gifts each year and the number of existing Merry Gentlemen dwindled each month. With only a dozen Merry Gentlemen left, it seemed as if the blessings had vanished, along with their good ways. In an effort of hope, they gathered for a yearly meeting to discuss what they would do with the lack of blessings in the world. More importantly, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span&gt;who&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span&gt; they would honor with the remaining blessings.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The golden light illuminating the dining hall did little to comfort the situation at hand. Among the eleven Merry Gentlemen sitting at the table, only ten of them talked amongst each other. They spoke for hours about how they would execute their plans. Or, their evil plans, as it seemed to the lone Merry at the far end of the table. The longer he listened to their conversation, the less merry they became. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;To them, the most apparent ones for joy were the most wicked and gruesome at heart. They were the ones who had all the riches in the world and had little knowledge of poverty. The ones who never knew what struggle was. The ones who didn’t even know what to be grateful for.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As the metal hand travelled around the clock, the lone Merry’s fist increasingly tightened. His irritation grew with each chime of the grandfather clock. It grew to the point he could no longer withstand the torture. Ice crystallized around the legs of his chair, his eyes piercing into the Merry at the other end of the table. Harsh words rang around the dining hall as he brought the horrors of their plans to light. Some turned their gaze to their laps while others let embers blaze behind their eyes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;“Merry Snow! Thou will cease these insanities at once!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Merry Snow gritted his teeth as the Merry on the other side of the table stood from his chair. Merry Byers; blessed to move within the shadows. Ice crept along Snow’s heals as Merry Byers extended his hand towards Snow.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;“I would not forget what we’ve discussed about the defects in thy nature.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ice crawled along the legs of the table as silence stiffened the room. Snow was disgusted Merry Byers had said those words as if he were worse. Perhaps he was right but, Snow would never utter the plans Merry Byers had proposed. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Snow stormed out of the dining hall into the corridors of the Estate. Frost ran along the carpet runners while the windows whistled. He could hear the commotion of the other Merrys banging against the dining hall’s frozen doors. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;He was almost at the end of the corridor when he heard the doors slam against the floor. He held his hands up and shards of ice erupted along the flooring of the corridor. A firm grip on his wrist jerked him around and he glared into Merry Byers’ eyes. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;“Shall I remind thee why thee are here?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Snow glanced towards the Merrys behind Merry Byers. Merry Ezekiel was careful with his flames while he tried to melt the sharp blades of ice. The others bickered with one another as they tried to find other ways to get to Snow. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;“It would be a pity if he were to see thee damage his safe haven.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A chill ran along the back of his neck as he watched Merry Byers’ lips curl into an unnerving smile. He kept his cold glare directed at Merry Byers as ice slithered across his arm. Merry Byers’ eyes widened as he watched the ice mold into thick spikes. With a snap of Snow’s fingers, piercing winds burst shards of glass from the frames of the windows into the corridor. Merry Byers’ grip snapped from Snow’s wrist and the winds tugged him into a whirlwind of glass. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;“Thy blazen filth!” Merry Byers shouted as shards tore at his clothing. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Snow watched as the wind dragged the Merrys down the hall as they clambered for any ledge to hold onto. A tree fell into the side of the corridor. Its branches reached towards Snow, only to be frozen into blue icicles. He turned towards the double doors and thrust his hand. A large surge of blue ice burst the doors open into the courtyard of the Estate. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;His heels clipped upon the cobblestone in strict rhythm as dark clouds swirled above the Estate. Frost ran along the hems of his clothing as the Estate surrendered to the storm. Ice encrusted the walls and windows of the Estate while tree branches snapped into the wind. His rhythmic steps continued throughout the Estate as he grew close to the East side.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;“Merry Snow?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Snow halted, the winds wavering as the small voice reached his ears. His cloak draped around him, hiding him in a pillar of darkness as he waited for the voice to speak again.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;“Have thee forgotten what tiding of comfort joy can bring?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Snow turned towards the voice. There, at the start of the corridor, stood perfection within the chaos of the storm. His olive-green eyes captivated him with his golden curls strategically places. There was nothing cold about this gentleman. Even with the whistling blizzard around them, Snow could feel the tug on his chest. He couldn’t believe how the winds refused to tug at the gentleman’s cream-colored cloak. Not even the flame upon the tip of his chamberstick flickered. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;“The world wishes nothing of it,” Snow replied. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;“What, in thou eye, defines the world?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;“What defines the world is power in which we do not have,” Snow said through gritted teeth.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;“Yet thee reign a storm over the innocent?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Snow inhaled, his breath seeping into his tense frame, “Has your flame never experienced the winds?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A soft smile peaked on the gentleman’s lips, “The joy I hold shall not be smothered by those who seek the worst of the world and thyselves.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As the winds grew stronger, his statement stayed true. The flame did not wither in the slightest. Snow stood before him, waiting for the flame to go out but it stubbornly stayed alight. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;“Why now do you appear?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;“Why now do thee flee at my first sight of thee? Have thou lost all reason to stay?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Snow’s brows furrowed in frustration. “Do you always speak in questions?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;“Not usually.” The gentleman stepped towards Snow, “Doth thou not recall what a Merry is to say?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Snow gritted his teeth, “Nothing I dismay will change their wickedness.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;“Dismay nothing of thee,” he corrected. “Let nothing steal thy joy. Joy cannot be gifted. It is an experience.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;“If you believe that there is truth in joy...” Snow took one long glance at the gentleman as he collected his words. “Don’t let the wicked rule what is righteous.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Snow pulled his cloak around him and continued through the arch at the end of the corridor. The gentleman bolted towards him, nearly losing his grip on his chamberstick. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;“Merry Snow!” the gentleman called out. He passed through the archway and stumbled into the snow outside. Layers of snow covered the expanse of the lawn with no footprints to be found. Snow had vanished within the storm.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
