      <title>Shifted Life</title>
      <link>https://www.scribblehub.com/series/1106255/shifted-life/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">38435a1c01f79cea22b1e23e3adc7f526ad6fa86</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 29 Jun 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;The world had found its calm and everything was going alright until one unassuming day in the year 2081 when the world was thrown into a new chaos, the world being affected by changes nobody could've seen coming. What would you do when your entire life is flipped on its head? How will the world react when something thought limited to books and games makes a society-shaking debut in reality? This is the story of one individual as they adapt to life in a changing world and possibly discover more about themselves along the way.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Disclaimer: Any similarities between characters in the story and people in real life are entirely unintentional. While I doubt it's needed here's a reminder that this book is completely fictional.&lt;br /&gt; The gore warning is only just in case. While there will be gore I don't intend on there being that much excessive gore.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;Chapter one: The beginining of it all&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;div class="wi_authornotes"&gt; &lt;div&gt; &lt;div class="p-avatar-wrap"&gt;&lt;a class="avatar has-link" href="/profile/164546/lace/"&gt;&lt;img id="acc_ava_change profile" alt="" src="https://cdn.scribblehub.com/avatar/s/41/ava_164546_1717227821.jpg"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="an_username"&gt;&lt;a href="/profile/164546/lace/"&gt;Lace&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div style="clear: both;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="wi_authornotes_body"&gt;  Edited!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Hi there, the author, Lace here! This is my first true work I'm putting out there and I realize I'm probably not the best on some aspects. That said, if you end up reading the whole thing please give me your thoughts and opinions in the comments section. I always welcome constructive criticism as it helps me get better at the writing I love, giving you readers better stories to read in turn. Based on the poll I've removed the color to keep it simple and easy for you all. we'll stay smooth like this going forward.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Ely, hey Ely. Get up.” Roused from the darkness of a dreamless sleep I opened my eyes and sat up as I looked around: I was in a classroom and it seemed class was over. Now I looked at who spoke to me: A muscular boy that’s about six-foot-one in height with somewhat scruffy ear length brown hair and beige skin, standing beside me and my desk dressed in his usual loose blue jeans and a plain black t-shirt, looking down at me with amethyst eyes. I don't know why but I felt my pulse quicken slightly whenever I noticed him looking at me. “Damn Ely, you never fall asleep at school. Did you even sleep last night?” It was my best friend named Lucas, a guy the same age as me that’s been by my side for nine years now.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I did but Barely.” I sat up straight and was about to take my phone from my pocket but a sudden rough voice made me stop with a full body flinch.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Mr. Vale, because of your history and your general performance I can overlook this incident this time but please try not to sleep through my class again. I’ll put together a note package for you to pick up at the end of the day. Have a good lunch.” The speaker was a male teacher in his late forties with one eye.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Thank you Mr. Garrick. Sorry for the trouble.” The bell for lunch rang out just as I finished speaking after which me and Lucas grabbed our bags and left the room, going and putting our stuff in our lockers before starting to head to the school cafeteria just like any other lunch break before.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;We were almost to our destination when someone came up behind me and spoke to me. “So how were the first five days of being eighteen?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:300"&gt;That voice… Along with something else.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Familiar feminine voice? Check. Sudden poke to my side? Check. “Uneventful and kinda boring. Hello Tamara.” I said as I rubbed where I just got a hard poke, looking to my right to see another friend now walking beside me. Tamara is a girl with a lighter skin tone and light brown hair reaching just under her shoulders, currently wearing black jogging pants and a purple hoodie with &lt;span style="text-decoration:underline"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Purple People Eater&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;on the back in white lettering, the girl’s green eyes scanning for new targets to poke. When it came to height she could be described as average.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Hello back at ya Ely. You and Lucas on the way to the cafeteria?” I nodded. “Sweet, I’m joining you.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I gave a slight shrug and smiled softly. She may be a chaotic lover of mischief but she’s fun to be around and I was curious about any news she had as she always had the latest around school. “So anything new?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Ms. L has a new cat that hangs out during class now. A few people are apparently oddly tired and warm today and also barely slept last night. That’s all the news so far.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:300"&gt;Barely slept last night, oddly tired, oddly warm? Maybe I should tell her to add me to that list.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; “Interesting…” That’s all I said as we arrived at the cafeteria and made our way to the counter to get some food.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“You’re still dating Toby, right?” Lucas asked as the lunch lady dished up and handed us a food tray each. “I haven’t seen him for a few days.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“He’s on a family trip, remember?” Tamara reached over and poked him as she spoke. “And yes,we’re still going out.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I chuckled and led the way to an empty table. “If I’m remembering it right he’s in Hawaii right now.” I commented as I sat down and wasted no time in digging into the shepherd’s pie that was today's lunch.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Hah! Nah, he’s way up on some mountain. His parents thought mountain climbing right now would be fun but kept it a surprise. I kind of feel bad for the guy.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Lucas almost choked on his food but managed to swallow only to laugh for a moment after. “I can’t wait to ask him how much he froze off! That kid can’t handle the cold for shit!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I finished another forkful of food before speaking again. “No, I think it’s just that you can handle temperatures like nobody’s business. Remember when you tried that ice dip competition last summer? You made everyone’s jaws drop while you got in and just swam around.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Okay I get it but I’m still gonna tease the guy about his trip.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Hell no! Only I get to tease Toby! Tease Ely dammit!” Tamara snapped and threw a pea at Lucas which he caught in his mouth and swallowed before grinning wide. I couldn’t help but laugh as Tamara groaned and resigned herself to glare at him as she ate her food. After a moment Tamara sighed and all three of us chuckled and ate the rest of our food quietly. Lucas finished first and went to put his tray in the right spot at the counter before he went to wait by the exit, Tamara finishing next and doing the same to end up standing beside Lucas while seeming to talk about something.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I finished last and stood up to walk to the counter but halfway I suddenly felt really heavy. Too heavy to move… I stopped and stumbled and the heavy feeling immediately disappeared only to be replaced by feeling as if my body was on fire. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:300"&gt;What’s happening? Why do I feel like this? It hurts dammit!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; “Ely? Are you good?” Lucas called it out but I barely heard it for some reason and not a moment after my pain tripled and I screamed, flickers of green light catching the corners of my vision as I suddenly realized that I could hear at least two others screaming out in pain just like I was. I passed out a second later and while it was all mere seconds it felt like a couple minutes at least.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;…&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;… …&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:300"&gt;Am I awake? I feel like I’m in a bed so I must be in the school’s nurse’s office.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; I opened my eyes to see a dull white ceiling above me. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:300"&gt;Wait… this isn’t the nurse’s office.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; My whole body felt stiff and heavy as well as weak and it took a surprising amount of effort to do it but I sat up before looking around the room: I was in a bed situated in the corner of the room farthest from the door, enough room between the bedside and the wall for someone to be able to sit in a chair, that was set there. A window was set into the wall beside my bed with curtains half closed, gentle sunlight shining in on the dull white and gray room. There was a small table at the foot of the bed with what seemed like some flowers about to wilt as well as a considerable number of cards. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:300"&gt;‘&lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:300"&gt;Get well soon’ cards I’d say… I’m pretty sure I’m in the hospital.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; Not far from the bed was one of those slim rolling tables to allow patients to eat while in bed. An office chair was the only other thing in the room though there were two doors to the room, a hall on the other side of one for sure and the other door likely leading to a bathroom.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;After looking around the room I then noticed a button on the side of the bed with a note taped to it - &lt;span style="text-decoration:underline"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;press if awake&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;. I pressed it but as I did I noticed my hand seemed slightly smaller than I remembered. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:300"&gt;Wait, how long was I out? It only felt like a day at first but now…&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; I straightened up and realized something. I realized that it wasn’t my whole body that felt heavy but in fact it was only my chest, the question of why coming to the forefront of my mind. I looked down at myself properly and felt as if my heart stopped for a moment. “What the fuck!?” I had on a hospital gown that was commonly worn by patients but I was more focused on a different detail that neither the gown or the blanket on my lower half was able to hide from my view. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:300"&gt;I have tits!? Why do I have tits!?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; I didn’t even need to touch them or anything to tell they were real but this made my mind go wild with confusion. “Why the hell do I have tits!?” Hearing my voice again another detail caught my attention as I covered my mouth in surprise. My voice wasn’t exactly deep before but it was certainly not as soft or high as this. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:300"&gt;What the fuck is going on!?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; The moment I asked myself that an older caucasian man dressed in the scrubs and white coat of a doctor walked in, his brown hair slightly graying and his amber eyes seeming tired. He closed the door behind himself while I worked hard internally to not loudly blurt out all the questions I had, to be polite and calm myself down. He had a clipboard and paper in his hands and a few things in the pockets of the white coat.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Hello there. I’m doctor Kalligan, the one who’s been watching over you here at the hospital.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:300"&gt;That confirms my thoughts of where at least.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; “I’m just going to do a couple small tests and ask a few questions now that you’re awake, okay?” I nodded as he pulled the office chair in the room over to the bedside and sat down. It was taking a lot of effort to keep my cool and not barrage him with questions but I was sure he’d give me the chance soon. “Keep your eyes open please. Do you feel any pain or soreness? Nausea? Anything else?” He pulled a small device from a pocket on his white coat and used it to check my eyes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I feel stiff, heavy. I feel pretty weak too but that’s it right now.” I blinked as he put the little device away and looked at his watch while taking a soft hold on my wrist, checking my pulse.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“That’s to be expected given the situation. Can you open your mouth for me?” He asked as he pulled another small device from a pocket, checking my mouth and throat before putting it away and speaking again. “Can you tell me what the last thing you remember before going unconscious is?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:300"&gt;Last thing I remember? It’s not something I really want to remember right now…&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; “Last thing I remember is being in the cafeteria at school. Me and a couple friends just finished lunch and I pretty much just stood up when I started to feel a strange weight over my whole body. It was enough to make me stop but it only lasted a few seconds before it turned into this burning pain. It felt like I was on fire.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The doctor nodded and wrote something on the paper clipped to the clipboard he had. “I’m just going to notify your parents that you’ve woken up. I’m sure you have plenty of questions so you can ask away once I get back, I’ll answer as best I can.” It was at this point that he stood up and left the room and a minute or two passed before he came back.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“So I can ask away now?” I asked as he came back in and sat in the office chair again. He nodded in response. “Then first off, why the hell do I have tits and why is my voice different than it was before?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I’ll have to explain a bit first to answer that. You were affected by an unknown energy. Contact seemed to put you into a coma-like state which you’ve been in for the last three months.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Wait, three months!? I’ve been out for three months!?” I immediately scolded myself mentally for interrupting him but the doctor didn’t seem phased at all and went back to explaining.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Yes. The energy that put you into the state you were in also seemed to cause a reaction in your body, making your body shift over time to be the opposite gender you were. The change is down to the genetic level in a way that it’s as if you were born as that gender which in your case is female.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“If that’s how it is then I don’t have my, uh, thing… down below anymore?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Correct, your penis is gone and you now have a vagina instead.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Oh well, not like I ever did anything with it anyway.” I mumbled to myself which seemed to earn a raised brow from the doctor before I asked my next question. “Was there anyone else that had this happen to them? I wasn’t the only one was I?” While remembering everything else I also remembered that I heard at least two other people scream out in pain before I had blacked out.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The doctor sighed. “No, you’re not the only one. It’s been estimated that forty percent of the world’s total population was affected by the same event and have been shifted to the opposite gender.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;After hearing that I stared at him for a moment before turning to look straight forward, becoming lost in thought about what must’ve changed in the time I was out. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:300"&gt;Good thing it’s 2081 and not 2032 or earlier cause society back then would’ve collapsed from this kind of situation judging from what I learned in history class. Anyway, back to the present and the issue at hand!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; “Is there a way to reverse it all, to get my male body back?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Not at this time” The doctor seemed to take on a more serious expression as he spoke this time.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Really? Nothing you can do? What about doing a gender reassignment treatment? That would work right?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I’m sorry but I can’t help you with this and I can’t say anything more on this topic.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Hearing that gave me the feeling that it was a decision from those higher than him and there was nothing I could do to change it. I sighed and took a short moment to calm myself. “That’s all the questions I think I have right now. Could I be alone till my parents get here please? Wait, before that though, am I able to get anything to eat? I’m actually kinda hungry.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Hunger is expected given your situation. I’ll get a nurse to bring you some food and in the meantime just press the same button you did after waking up if you need anything.” With that the doctor stood up and put the chair he sat on back before exiting the room, letting me think in silence for a few minutes and get my bearings so to speak. It wasn’t long before a nurse came in with a tray of food, putting it down on the rolling table nearby and moving said rolling table to the bed. I thanked the nurse before they left, pulling the table a bit closer and starting to eat the food I was given&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;…&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:300"&gt;Wow, I'm hungrier than I thought.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; I had to remind myself again and again to eat slowly but even then the food was gone quickly and so I pushed the table away a bit and laid back down. With nothing else to do I simply thought and thought some more but it didn’t take long for me to feel restless, sitting up and moving to sit with my legs hanging off the bed. I stood up and immediately found myself more than a little weak, stumbling and barely managing to stay standing but I did it. Step after uneasy step I started to regain some semblance of balance while I slowly walked around a bit and while my legs weren’t any stronger in such a short time I was adjusting bit by bit. After a few minutes I heard the door start to open and turned to see my mom and dad coming into the room: My mother was about five-foot-four with brown shoulder length hair and pale skin, her light brown eyes casting a worried gaze over me at the moment. My father stood at six feet tall with ear length dark red hair(always slicked back for some reason) and tan skin, tired looking blue eyes looking over me before going to other things in the room. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:300"&gt;Wait, they recognize me, right?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; This fear was almost instantly soothed as my mom rushed over to me and pulled me into a hug, crying silently as my father stayed back and closed the door, both of my parents not saying a word yet. “Um, mom. Can you let me sit down please. I'm feeling pretty weak and unsteady right now.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:300"&gt;Not to mention it feels a little bit odd getting hugged with how my body is now.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She let go and stepped back with a slow nod and wiped away her tears. “The doctor said you’re fine medically but how do you feel?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;As she let go I steadied myself before walking over and sitting back on the bed. “Well, umm… I guess I’m still wrapping my head around, y’know, everything.” I leaned back and stared up at the ceiling for a moment then straightened back up. “Still doesn’t feel quite real. I mean I know it is real but yeah, it still doesn’t feel like it. To me I was just at school in the cafeteria a few hours ago but then I hear from the doctor that it’s actually been three months and I-” I sighed and took a deep breath in, letting it out slowly before I kept going. “Honestly I don’t know how I feel about all this. I can’t seem to think straight about it right now either. Right now I just wanna go home and eat. I’m so damn hungry right now…”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I’ll talk to the doctor about you getting discharged then.” My father said and turned to leave. As he was about to open the door it seemed someone was coming in first, the doctor from before opening the door to find himself face to face with my dad. “Perfect timing! My kid’s wanting to go home so I was wondering if he can be discharged or if he has to wait.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The doctor slipped to the side to stand closer to me and my mother. “They can be discharged today, yes, however we have a couple things left to do. Also I highly advise that they eat increased portions for the next few days. Their body needs to restock all the nutrients and energy used during the state of hyper growth they went into during the last third of the gender shift process but also so they can regain any muscle mass lost due to being in a coma-like state for the last three months.” He then looked straight at my mom and took a step closer to her. “Also, ma’am, given that this change made their body no different than as if they were born female I suggest that you, as their mother, teach them about certain things.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;My father looked utterly confused at this but then again, I was also quite confused. “Wait, what certain things are you talking about?” My dad took a step towards my mother as he spoke.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Things you have no part in.” My mom said as she glanced at my dad then looked back to the doctor. “Thank you so much for this, seriously. How long till we can take her home?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:300"&gt;Hold on… Did mom just call me a “her”? What the fuck!? She didn’t even ask if I was okay with being referred to with different pronouns!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt; &lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I gripped the bedding under me tightly in my fists as I kept myself quiet while the doctor responded to my mom’s question. “The things we have to do shouldn’t take too long. We’ll be taking a bit of blood, checking their blood pressure, doing a quick body scan and recording changes in height and weight. We already have the room for the scan ready so we’ll be doing that first whenever your child is ready.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Hun, I’m going to drive back and grab some clothes for our &lt;/span&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;son&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b&gt;.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; Do you want to come with me?” With how he spoke I realized that my dad most likely noticed how I felt about my mother calling me a ‘her’ at the time and I knew immediately that he wasn’t going to try and force me to accept my new physical gender. Knowing this made me feel relieved in a way but at this point he turned his gaze to me. “Ely, what clothes do you want me to grab you?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Um… I’d like a pair of my cargo pants and one of my T-shirts please. doesn’t matter which ones.” I glanced down at myself before a thought came to mind. “Can you grab a belt and one of my hoodies too please? Preferably the one I always wear when I’m chilling at home.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“You got it, I’ll see if I find that one for you. Me and your mom will be back soon.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Thanks dad.” I wanted to give him a hug before he left but I remembered how odd it felt when my mom gave me one and decided not to give him a hug right now.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;My parents shared a look as they left that told me they were going to have quite the ‘talk’ later on though my thoughts on this matter were quickly interrupted. “Now that your parents are off, would you be up for going through the things I mentioned to your parents?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Yeah, I’m up for it, so let’s get started please. I really wanna go home and the sooner the better.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Then please follow me.” The doctor led me out of the room and into a corridor which we went along till we got to a set of elevators, taking one down a couple floors before getting off and going down another corridor until we stopped to enter a room. I didn’t care enough to check what the room was labeled because I remembered the doctor told my parents that a body scan was up first. “Please lay down on the scan table Vale, with your head toward the scanner ring.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The only thing the room had in it was what looked like a big white slab with a big white ring set at the one end, this ring visibly set on a track to allow it to move along the length of the so-called scan table. I went up and, to my surprise, as I laid down I found that the top was actually a soft and almost gel-like material that made it somewhat comfy laying there. I hadn’t noticed till then but the doctor went into a connected room that had a viewing window to observe through. A moment after I laid down I heard a soft whirring sound as the scanning machine turned on and the ring lit up with a gentle blue glow and seemed as if it started to spin as it slowly moved along from one end of the table to the other twice, going back to its original position with the machine beeping and turning off a moment later. While it felt like an eternity I knew it was only a few minutes at most.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Okay, you can get up now. Take a moment if you need to before we head back up.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“One question.” I got up with a sigh and grabbed my hair to put it over my shoulder. “I don’t why I didn’t notice this till I laid down there but why is my hair so long now? It wasn’t even long enough to reach the bottom of my neck before, let alone past my shoulders. I don’t care if you tell me with fancy terms and stuff, I’m pretty sure I’ll understand it all.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Mhmm. The hair length would be a side effect of your body going through a state of hyper growth during the last month of the three you were unconscious for.” The doctor spoke as we started to walk back to the room I woke up in.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“What actually happened in those three months I was out for? To my body I mean. I may not be a doctor but I still know a person can’t just magically turn into the opposite gender, at least not without a proper biological process. I understand my body went into a sort of super growing mode for the last month but given my current state that means I had to go into a state of hyper regression or something similar.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Well you’re not quite wrong. I guess I can explain how the three months went from my understanding and all, if you want to hear it all.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I wanna hear it all please. I’m actually kinda curious not just because it happened to me but also cause the whole thing happened, period.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Well when it first happened we took blood samples from everyone affected and while it might sound unbelievable we found that everyone’s DNA had already changed. The unknown energy is suspected to have done it before the affected person even passed out. After they were brought to a hospital for care and possible treatment the body underwent what we understand as biological preparation for the changes to come which lasted all of the first month. After that the body went into a process of half regression over the course of the second month.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Half regression?” I thought for a moment before continuing. “I’m gonna hazard a guess here. Things like the penis and stuff, all the primary gender characteristics, pretty much got gone. Secondary stuff like extra body hair on guys or a girls, uh… chest… would’ve gone away too. That said, as just a half regression, aside from all that the body as a whole wouldn't have regressed to an earlier state, right?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Well now. You’re surprisingly sharp aren’t you?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“You’ve probably read my file and already know this but I’ve always been weaker than most so I make up for it by keeping my mind as good as I can get it. Brains before brawn, kind of. I do what I can do.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I did read your file, yes. As for your guess though, it’s rather accurate. The affected didn’t revert to anything like an infantile state however both primary and secondary sexual characteristics regressed until they were essentially non-existent. In many cases height was lost too. Anyway, at the end of the month the person was physically genderless, and very androgynous if I might add, which was where the third and seeming last month came in. The state of hyper growth began, primary sexual characteristics of the new gender appeared and developed before-”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Hold on a moment. So I was literally a neuter between the second and third month? That’s a weird thought to me honestly. Sorry about that, please continue.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The doctor smirked and chuckled softly as we stopped near the central desk of the floor my room was on.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:300"&gt; Wait, what? I didn’t even notice we went into the elevator or anything. huh. I’d ask why we stopped at the desk but I already know. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“It’s fine but how about we continue this talk when your blood pressure is checked. For now though please step onto the scale.” He motioned to a weight scale set beside the wall near the floor management desk. I did as asked and after a moment the thing made a soft beep before the doctor looked at what the scale read and wrote the result down on clipboard and paper.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I got curious and looked too though it was always somewhat tricky reading upside down. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:300"&gt;One hundred forty two point six pounds. Huh… &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I think I only lost a pound, maybe two…”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Well to be honest you were rather light for a eighteen year old boy.” I hadn’t realized I spoke the last of my thoughts out loud until he made the comment. “Could you step off and up against the stadiometer?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:300"&gt;Stadiometer? I’m assuming it has something to do with height given I just got my weight measured. Probably the wall ruler thing they always use. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I pointed to the object in question and asked: “You mean the wall ruler thing?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The doctor sighed. “Yes… The wall ruler thing.” I got in position with it so the doctor could record my height as well.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“So what’s my height now? I sure as hell know I’m shorter than I was.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:300"&gt;Kinda hard to miss that fact when I used to be taller than my mom. Now I’m just a tiny bit shorter I think.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“According to your file you were five feet and eight inches tall but now you are five feet and three inches tall. I can give you that in centimeters if you’d like.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I’m fine with feet and inches, thank you. I’m not much of a centimeter person.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:300"&gt;Five foot three… I’m an inch shorter than mom now. Great. Lucas will probably tease me about my height when he sees me. Wait… ya know what, let’s shove that next thought aside till later, okay me?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Very well then. Let’s get you back to your room now.” My room wasn’t far and I sat on the bed as soon as I got in, my legs feeling tired at the moment. “I’ll be right back with the equipment.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Finding myself alone in the room again I took a look around like I did when I first woke up and then flopped onto my back, shooting upright again at the alien feeling of my new chest bouncing slightly, groaning as I looked down at my front. “Yeah… These are real alright.” I sighed as I wondered what my life would be like from now on though I wasn’t thinking about that much longer before the doctor came back in with the equipment to check my blood pressure and such.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I believe we were supposed to finish the conversation we were having before we checked your weight and height. Would you like to get back to that?” He brought the equipment to the bedside and wrapped the black inflating part around my arm as he spoke then turned it on.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Yes please, though there’s probably not much left to say is there? You covered the first two months already but if the third month only just ended there’s probably not much solid data or anything.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“You are correct but I’ll cover what we know. So… after the second month ended with the affected left genderless and androgynous the body then entered a state of extremely fast growth and the new gender made itself visible. First thing to happen was the appearance and growth of the new primary sexual characteristics: New females acquired a vagina, a uterus and even ovaries, leaving them fully capable of reproduction. New males gained a penis and testicles which means they are also fully capable of the male side of reproduction.” He paused for a moment to take the black wrap thing off my arm and wrote the results on a paper as he continued. “After the primary characteristics were identifiable the secondary characteristics came along the same as they would in a natural puberty even if it was on fast forward. Females had breasts grow out and the androgynous appearance became more feminine. We’re assuming their voices changed as well in all cases. Males saw their respective changes as well with becoming more masculine in appearance, varying degrees of genital growth and body hair. Regardless of gender there was also the side effect of the hair on the head growing with the same increase in speed though I believe you already knew about that.” I nodded. “To be honest we had to have someone cut your hair twice throughout the whole process, otherwise it’d be past your feet right now.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“And my hair is still this long now!? Wow…” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The doctor was just finished packing up the equipment as someone knocked on the door with a male nurse poking their head in the room a moment later. “Excuse me, Vale’s parents are back.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The doctor let out an exasperated sigh and looked straight at them as he motioned toward me. “Don’t tell me that, let the kid know and let them in. Ely is right here.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The nurse flinched a little at the doctor’s irritated tone then looked at me. “Vale, your parent’s are here.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I know, thank you.” I watched them leave and close the door before glancing at the doctor. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:300"&gt;He seems like a pretty patient guy so he must’ve dealt with that person a lot today. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Are they new?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I’m not gonna hide or deny it: they’re very new. With the sheer scope of this whole event and how many people were affected we had to take on all the hands to help we could, even if they haven’t finished medical school. Like I said before, It’s estimated that forty percent of the entire world’s population had the same thing happen to them.” He took a deep breath and regained his composure. “Sorry about that. I’ll make a note and save your bloodwork for another day. Seeing as your parents probably brought clothes you should get dressed and get home. Have a good day, stay safe out there.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Thank you, I hope you have a good day as well.” I watched as he left and couldn't help but feel he meant something more when he said to stay safe. I was already almost mentally overloaded, partially of my own fault with asking him to explain all that he did, so I simply shrugged the thought aside while my parents came into the room. My father came in first and straight over to me to hand me the clothes I asked for: a pair of brown cargo pants and a belt, a black t-shirt with a depiction of a beach at sunset on the front, a pair of underwear and a pair of socks too. There was also a large baggy hoodie, a very dark blue in color with the picture of an old wooden ship at sea on the chest. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:300"&gt;Sweet, dad found the one I wanted!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; My mom came in just after him but she looked somewhat frustrated. “Thanks dad. I’m just gonna get changed in the bathroom there and then we can go I guess.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I stood up and made my way over to the door I assumed led to a bathroom and opened it to have my assumptions confirmed, stepping in and closing the door behind me to then stand in the middle of the room in front of the mirror over the sink. I looked in the mirror and felt like I was looking at another person, bringing a hand to my face to feel the difference. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:300"&gt;At least some things stayed the same I guess. SIlver lining there if nowhere else… &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;My skin was as beige as it ever was, my eyes were the same light brown I remember them being and my hair was still the dark shade of red it's been my whole life. It did seem to reach just about the middle of my back now though. I stared at my reflection a moment longer before tearing my gaze away and starting to get undressed, resisting the urge to check out my new body in the mirror as I attempted to put on a pair of my underwear only to find they didn’t fit at all anymore, the pair of boxers simply refusing to stay up. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:300"&gt;Okay, yeah… I should’ve expected that. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I skipped that step and put on the cargo pants and found I needed the belt just like I thought I would, putting on the t-shirt next with one thought popping into my head. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:300"&gt;It’s tight… &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I already knew the reason as I stared at my chest for a long moment before wrenching my mind back on track and putting on the socks my dad brought as well, finding them loose compared to before. Now that I was somewhat properly dressed I slipped on my hoodie to find the sleeves baggier and longer on me than I remembered which I expected but the torso was a little less baggy than I thought it would be, still being a bit bigger on me than before thanks to my body being smaller. All that was left then was to carefully slip my hair out from under my shirt and hoodie.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Now finished dressing I exited the bathroom and put the hospital gown I was wearing on the bed before putting the now too big to fit underwear in my hoodie pouch and looking at my father. “Umm, the underwear don't fit anymore.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;My father nodded and then both him and my mother looked me over from head to toe with their gazes settling on my feet for a few long seconds. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:300"&gt;It’s the socks, isn't it? They are visibly loose so it's definitely the socks. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;My mom looked at my dad while he let out a sigh of defeat. “I told you Ely would need these.” My mom handed me a pair of adjustable sandals as she spoke but the way she said it made it sound like she just tasted the sweetest victory ever.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;As I took the sandals I noticed my dad was holding a pair of my running shoes and I looked at the sandals I now held. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:300"&gt;Sandals huh? If it's been three months then it would be July now. Summer… &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Hey mom, dad, I hadn’t thought about this till now but what day is it?” I asked as I put the sandals on and adjusted them to fit.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“July fifth. It's Friday today.” My mom replied as I stood up once more. “Are you ready to go?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Yeah, I'm ready to go.” I walked with my parents to the elevators and took one down to an underground parking lot where there was a man and a woman dressed in what looked like expensive tailored black suits, standing beside a long black car. “Seriously, you brought the limo? I thought you drove here dad?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“To be fair I drove here the first time and back for your clothes but then your-”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I felt it would be better for you to make the trip home in comfort.” My mom interrupted as she gestured for me to get in, the female beside the limo opening the door for me to enter followed by my parents before she came in as well. The four of us took our seats in the surprisingly spacious vehicle while the man that had also been beside the limousine got into the driver seat and started up the vehicle. I could barely notice us starting to move without looking out a window.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Along the way I noticed a certain ad flash onto an electronic billboard: &lt;span style="text-decoration:underline"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;“Blue Cloud Industries &amp;amp; Technologies. Striving toward the future and building the foundation!”&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; My mom and dad were pictured on either side of the message. It was an ad for the company my parents founded together, the company being named after a unique kind of stone. My grandmother on my mom’s side first discovered the stone at the very bottom of the ocean. That said I sometimes wondered how they got the business worldwide before they were even forty. At those times I look at how smart my mom is and how good with people my dad usually is, looking at the things they've done as well, and then I understand again.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;At this point the rest of the trip and my thoughts just seemed to blend together…&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
