      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Three beings all connected to each other in some shape or form take on separate challenges in life in this odd post-apocalyptic world. One is a great scientist who can build living weapons from the ground up, he's figuring out how to fix this broken world and defend it from larger-than-life threats. The second one is one of his creations, a beast made for killing, but she desires to live a life of music and performance. The last is one of the four monarchs that rule this world, dealing with the everlasting stress of holding an entire kingdom upright and in order. Whichever one you root for is up to you, but you might not like the details of each one, as none of them are perfect, as all 3 of them have innocent blood on their hands.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;Chapter one-Stress&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;h3&gt;⇒ King Hayleet Mason Ψ&lt;/h3&gt; &lt;p&gt;"King Hayleet! There's damage to floor fifty, housing unit 47997" I hear as I stir awake. My eyes still half open I look to the side of my bed, looking at the clock on my bedside table. It was 3:19 sol&lt;sup class="modern-footnotes-footnote" data-mfn="1"&gt;&lt;a href="javascript:void(0)" &gt;1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;span class="modern-footnotes-footnote__note" data-mfn="1"&gt;The term for day&lt;/span&gt;. Feeling the damaged tower on my side, I let out a loud groan and sit up. I look down at myself and notice a green glow on where my left side would be if it existed. I look towards the phantoon&lt;sup class="modern-footnotes-footnote" data-mfn="2"&gt;&lt;a href="javascript:void(0)" &gt;2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;span class="modern-footnotes-footnote__note" data-mfn="2"&gt;A Crocidillian race that consists of a Head, Floating hands, Legs, and a tail. they usually wear long cloaks to hide their nonexistent bodies. &lt;/span&gt; calling me, it was a dusty phantoon, his scales were a grey-brown color and were speckled with darker colored brown. He had a clipboard with at least eighteen pages attached to it. I soon recognized him as one of the CEOs of the construction unit. His cloak looked roughed up and covered in dirt and grime. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I finally open my mouth to speak, "What kind of damage are we talking about?". I get up and walk to my closet to change out of my pajama pants into my cloak. I close the door and pick my floor dragging cloak. I quickly take off my pj's and put the cloak around me, making more of my hands appear in the air to aid me in getting dressed. I walk out of the closet, my cloak dragging along the floor making a soft slithering noise as it does so. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Kitchen fire got out of control and spread to 5 houses, sir. Nobody was injured but the damage is pretty bad," he said as he flips through his clipboard pages. "you reckon your tower guardian form could help with the damage?" he looked up at me. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;While my extra hands mingle with the crown case, I stare daggers into his eyes. I simply reply with a stern "no." and he seemed to understand the concept. I get the crown from its case and I place it on my head. I storm out towards the elevator to go fix the damage done. The CEO joins me. As the elevator descends, I look out the window, looking down at all the civilians within the tower. They were all going about their daily lives without much care in the world. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I rub my eyes and yawn, still tired from waking up early, and not having any breakfast. The CEO turns to me, with a worried look, "Are you okay, sir?" he says softly, drifting his focus away from his clipboard. I look at him, shaking my head no. I wasn't really in the talking mood because I was woken up at the asscrack of sol to come fix a mild error that the people were a bit too stupid to solve on their own. At this point, I should just make being an idiot a crime.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The CEO looks back at his clipboard as if he was trying to keep himself from worrying too much about me. He's always had a habit of worrying about every little thing. He talks to himself quietly as he writes some prices on the clipboard. I don't understand how people can be living a life of just numbers and values, paperwork and bills. How is he content with his life like this? I always hold off signing permission forms until the end of every sol. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I dismiss those thoughts as the elevator finally reaches the unit. I walk out, addressing the damage.  I signal to the CEO to get everybody out of the way. He nodded and ran to the crowds of people, ushering them out using telekinetic magic. When everyone was out, he signaled me to to go do my duty. With that, I run through the smoke and ash and jump into the air. I extend my hands outwards and send a massive water geyser out from them, extinguishing the flame. All the bystanders were absolutely soaked, and there was a mild flood as a result of the sheer amount of water I spat out. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I land on the ground, from their faces it seemed like I was pissed. Well, I was pissed. I walk up to the crowd, picking out the owner of the house. I look down at him, a scowl forming on my face. He was a dusty lavender phantoon, his pale purple scales with almost white splotches randomly speckled about his face made him look like something straight out of a fantasy book. He seemed to be a teenager, definitely still in school.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"What the fuck were you thinking?!" I roared at him, bearing my teeth. I let out a threatening growl. "You know fire magic is the last one taught in school for this reason!" I lift him up by his hoodie. The teen whimpered, covering his face.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"I'm sorry, my stove broke and I didn't have the fangets&lt;sup class="modern-footnotes-footnote" data-mfn="3"&gt;&lt;a href="javascript:void(0)" &gt;3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;span class="modern-footnotes-footnote__note" data-mfn="3"&gt;The currency in Dreavil. They're small square coins with a hole cut in the middle. The Smaller the hole, the more it's worth.&lt;/span&gt; to get it fixed!" The kid looked as if he was about to cry. I didn't feel bad. Third time this month some moron set their house on fire. I'm sick and tired of the burning pain and the whole hassle of fixing the situation because the folks are all morons.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"No. You're going to jail for a week. You broke the law of using fire magic without proper certification. No arguments." I hissed. The CEO looked at me like I was crazy. "Go back to work." I immediately snapped. Without a word, he nodded and headed for an elevator. I take the teenager to another elevator. I press the button to floor 79, and the doors close. "Now listen here. You had no right to do that."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The teen kept looking down. "I know" He whined. He looked at me finally and opened his mouth to speak. His teeth had blue and yellow braces on them. "Are you gonna tell my moms about this?" He said worriedly.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I burst out laughing. "Are you fucking serious?!" I said in between laughs, "Does a tar stalker sleep in tar!?"&lt;sup class="modern-footnotes-footnote" data-mfn="4"&gt;&lt;a href="javascript:void(0)" &gt;4&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;span class="modern-footnotes-footnote__note" data-mfn="4"&gt; Dreavil for the saying "does a bear shit in the woods"&lt;/span&gt;. I look away from the kid, still laughing. People these days are truly dumb. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Shit..." The teen said to himself.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Play stupid games, win stupid prizes." I chuckle. The elevator eventually reached the floor. I dragged him by his hoodie to the police station. I approach the office and speak with an officer. "This kid was playing with fire without a certification. Parents live on unit 47997." I say, turning my heel. I heard the shouts of the teen, begging for forgiveness and how sorry he was. I didn't want to hear it. I'm tired enough.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I walk back into the elevator, to go do more work. I'm in there with an elderly lady. She was a snow phantoon with red eyes, she was using a cane to walk. She had large glasses, and her horns were long and curled. I always found it interesting how no two phantoons looked the same. there was always some variation. I myself am an emperor emerald phantoon. Emperor phantoons earn their name due to their size, being the largest ones. The emerald comes from the deep green color these kinds have throughout their bodies. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The elevator comes to a stop, I let the elderly phantoon go, before heading out myself. I was in the food marketplace on floor 300. I needed a proper breakfast. Speaking of, I look at the clock, it was 4:45 sol. Still early. Looking around I spot a restaurant that has breakfast items on the menu. Upon sitting down, a waiter walks to my table. He smiles.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The emerald phantoon speaks "Hello king, what shall I get for you today?". He pulls out a notepad and looks at me. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Bexyberry&lt;sup class="modern-footnotes-footnote" data-mfn="5"&gt;&lt;a href="javascript:void(0)" &gt;5&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;span class="modern-footnotes-footnote__note" data-mfn="5"&gt; a cyan raspberry&lt;/span&gt; waffles with some millven &lt;sup class="modern-footnotes-footnote" data-mfn="6"&gt;&lt;a href="javascript:void(0)" &gt;6&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;span class="modern-footnotes-footnote__note" data-mfn="6"&gt;a 6-legged boar that lives in caves&lt;/span&gt; bacon. To drink I'll have some lousik&lt;sup class="modern-footnotes-footnote" data-mfn="7"&gt;&lt;a href="javascript:void(0)" &gt;7&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;span class="modern-footnotes-footnote__note" data-mfn="7"&gt;a large purple fruit that looks like a pineapple and jackfruit hybrid.&lt;/span&gt; juice. That'll be all sir, thank you." I say. He grins and walks off.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I summon my laptop and open it up. I open some documents and begin to type. I type fast, writing in data about energy consumption and prices to make more. Boring stuff. After that's done, I open my emails to see how many pathetic complaints I had. There was only 1 email though. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;What's weirder is its from a weather research facility that's in the Kyballak mountains. It had one attachment, and the heading for the email was titled 'There's something up here.'. Upon opening the email, there was a hastily written short paragraph. It read: Something is in here, we're in DDanger, itshungry anf it'd looking for me. killedthe rest of the fatility. lastone herne. Shernd Help. itg coming tih coming.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;That's concerning. I open the file, and it was a blurry picture of what looked like some cybernetic monster attacking one of the workers. It had glowing eyes that were purple and yellow, with what looked to be spikes running down it's dorsal, of which gleamed purple. It had 6 legs, all mechanical. It looked like a cat of sorts. Based on the image, I could guess it was about nine feet tall.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"What is that..." I mutter to myself, looking closely at the image. I could notice it had a mechanical jaw, with metal teeth. There was a large intestine stuck in it's mouth, hanging out like some twisted flag. It's claws were coated in blood and organ matter. Whatever this thing is, it was deadly. I eventually noticed something familiar on the creature's arm.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Crystal Ball Mechanic's logo.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Crystal Ball was a highly respected prosthetics and robotic organ replacement company. Why would their logo be on such a heinous beast? That's the opposite of their goal, to give people a chance at life, not rip them away. I was even friends with the CEO, Stryker. Smart man. He loved helping others with their injuries. He himself had a prosthetic arm. He wore a mask as he didn't want his scarred face exposed. Was Stryker aware of this? Was it just a bad warehouse? What was it?&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I heard someone calling my name but I was too focused. What caused this? Who made it? Why? What is this thing capable? How does this thing exist? Why does it kill?&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"King Hayleet!" I heard after snapping out of it. "Your food's here" It was the waiter. I stare blankly, before taking the plates. "Are you okay sir?" He asked. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Yeah, sorry, caught up in my work," I reply, "Thank you." I grasp my fork and proceed to eat my breakfast, looking at the picture. I changed to a tab that had a map. I went to where the weather research facility was, and funnily enough, Crystal Ball's HQ was 5 miles away from it. Stryker definitely knew about this. If it came from the HQ then Stryker had to have a part in this monster. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I finish my breakfast and teleport my laptop away, while summoning my gun-swords&lt;sup class="modern-footnotes-footnote" data-mfn="8"&gt;&lt;a href="javascript:void(0)" &gt;8&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;span class="modern-footnotes-footnote__note" data-mfn="8"&gt;A Popular Dreavish weapon, a sword with a shotgun within its handle. &lt;/span&gt;. I set down a bag of fangets for payment for the food, and I walk out of the restaurant. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;As I'm heading to the elevator, I summon my announcement mic, which tells a message through the whole tower.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"This is an important announcement. All phantoons in levels 34 thousand and below, please evacuate to a higher level. there is a threat that is beyond anything else. Thank you." I make the mic disappear. I shuffle through the crowds of people trying to get to the higher levels of the tower, making it to my personal elevator.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;On the way down, the thoughts of what that thing was continued to haunt me. I had no idea of how powerful it was. What it'd do to me. What it'd do to my people. What it'd do to the other kingdoms. I couldn't let this thing hurt anyone else. I needed to stop it, otherwise everything I hold dear could be absolutely demolished.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The elevator made it to the last floor, and for the first time in my life, I was in the desert. Ruins of old kingdoms are scattered everywhere. It felt familiar but, I had never been here before. I shake it off and walk towards the Mountains, being careful to not step in any sandslink traps. My swords were holstered on my back, ready to attack at any moment. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I looked at one of the ruins, it looked like a castle, and it felt oddly homey. The torn-up castle was pretty big, it had dragon claw marks on it. Those made me feel a feeling of dread. What is this? Why is it so oddly familiar? I've spent my whole life in the tower, so why this feeling? I don't have any memory of this place.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I guess I'll never know.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
