    <item>
      <title>The Dreamers Wake</title>
      <link>https://www.scribblehub.com/series/1106918/the-dreamers-wake/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">5dbf02602f9c4343f13903915aaf66b84d086687</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 01 Jun 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Life is going just fine, Elster and Ariane have a cozy apartment on Rotfront, they're living happy domestic and professional lives, they have each other and more.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;And then someone left behind finds them.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;Full Story&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;div id="workskin"&gt; &lt;div id="chapters"&gt; &lt;div class="userstuff"&gt; &lt;p&gt;A lone figure shuffled through the line of apartment rooms until she reached her door. Clad in a thick, black winter coat, a scarf, tuque, insulated pants, and boots. She gave herself one last shake and kicked her boots together to get as much of the Rotfront snow off herself as possible before slipping her key in the door and stepping inside. She could hear the faint sounds of a sports game playing on the television along with the pleasing sounds of humming and something sizzling away in the kitchen.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Ari! I’m home with the groceries!”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“...Ellie? I’ll be there in just a second!”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster smiled as she put her bags down and started removing her winter fare. She hung her tuque, scarf, and coat on the coat rack by the front door to the apartment, leaving her upper body clad in a simple, gray, ribbed sweater as she gave her stomach and neck-length brown hair tied into a short ponytail a quick rub. She grabbed her bag of groceries again and was about to step into the kitchen just past the living room when she abruptly stopped at an unknown and alien sight.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;There was someone else sitting on their couch watching the television.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She was a frankly gargantuan woman, at least two and a half metres tall with hair that cascaded down more than half that length, clad in a black leather jacket and scuffed jeans and with a golden wreath adorning her head. She sat on the couch with her knees almost as high as her shoulders, given her height, and sipped from a bottle of non-alcoholic lager using a long, bendy straw.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She also looked at Elster the moment she noticed her, and gave her a short, awkward wave, which Elster just as awkwardly returned on instinct.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She looked familiar to Elster, but she had difficulty figuring out why. At least until she looked down at where her feet would be and found only stumps.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster took a step back and offered a confused and perplexed frown just as Ariane walked into the living room wearing a smudged, white, chef’s apron and still holding her spatula in hand. She saw Elster’s shock and confusion at the guest in their apartment and immediately stepped forward to make things clear.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Ah, Ellie, we have… a visitor.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster looked at Ariane and nodded. “I can see.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane walked up to the middle point separating the two and smiled. “Ellie, I’d like you to meet Falke.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster looked at the two-hundred-and-fifty-centimetre-tall Replika clad in clothes, who took the straw out from her lips after a couple of seconds of awkward staring.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Hi, Ellie,” she greeted in a rather deep and low-pitched voice. “Nice to finally meet you.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster blinked rapidly and started to take a step to the side just as Ariane moved up to her and rubbed her shoulder.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“She knows,” Ariane whispered to her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster’s frown quickly dropped as she looked looked into Ariane’s crimson eyes with her own, brown eyes. “About us? The gate? The mission?” she quickly and quietly asked.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Everything,” Ariane answered.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;They both heard Falke start to stand up, and Ariane stepped to the side to open up Elster’s view. Her head ended just a hand’s width from the ceiling, but she didn’t seem to mind as she approached the two while rubbing her titanium hands together.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Would you… like some help in putting away the groceries?” she asked, her voice still deep and low in register but sounding very careful and hesitant.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster froze, not knowing how to respond to their guest. Ariane kept her hand on her shoulder but moved to be closer to the middle between the two, alternating her gaze between them. Eventually, Falke lightly cleared her throat and spoke again.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Was it… inappropriate to refer to you by that name earlier? Would you prefer if I just used ‘Elster’?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She bit her lip for a moment before finally stepping off the welcome mat to their apartment. “I think… I need to have a conversation with my wife… in private,” she replied.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke nodded and stepped out of the way. “I completely understand. I am aware of how… awkward this must feel…” she said, pausing to swallow lightly. “It took me… a considerable amount of time to summon the willpower to… make myself known to you.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster nodded back and she and Ariane walked past Falke, with Elster trailing just behind, holding her hand.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Oh, wait,” Falke called out once they were in the middle of the living room. They both peered back over their shoulders.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke pointed to the bag of groceries Elster left by the door. “I can put those away for you if you like.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This time, Ariane spoke up. “That would be lovely, Falke, thank you,” she said, hastily adding, “Oh, but, leave the yakisoba noodles out, please!”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke smiled and gave them a thumbs-up as she carried the bag into the kitchen. Ariane turned back to Elster and mouthed a silent, ‘Come on’ as she led her into their shared bedroom. Once inside, Ariane sat down at the edge of their bed while Elster shut the door behind them.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“So-”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I’ve never met her before, Ellie,” Ariane blurted out, raising her hands and letting them fall to her sides. “She just… knocked on the door about half an hour ago, introduced herself, called me by my name, and said she knew us… Scout Officer Ariane Yeong and LSTR-512, that is.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster stood by the door and nodded silently. A few seconds later she joined Ariane by sitting next to her on the bed. There they sat silently for a while, with Elster only breaking the awkwardness by clumsily lifting her legs to pull her boots off.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“That wasn’t all she knew, by the way,” Ariane added once Elster’s feet were back on the ground.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“She has your memories?” Elster asked, turning toward her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane met Elster’s eyes and blinked a few times before letting out a quiet, “Huh.” She scooted herself a little closer to Elster and rested her head against her shoulder. “How did you know that?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster found Ariane’s hand atop her lap and squeezed it. “Because I have seen her before when I was travelling through Sierpinski looking for you. She was in a coma… and I took a peek at what I think was her journal. She described going through the gate and coming back… polluted… by another person’s memories.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Polluted is a rather harsh word,” Ariane commented. She closed her eyes as she rested against her wife. “All through my talk with her she was only kind, polite, and gentle. Doesn’t sound like someone who’s mind was polluted.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Maybe she just feels better about it now,” Elster suggested.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Perhaps, yeah.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Hmm.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;They each took a moment to lean on each other. The temptation to fall back into bed and hold each other was intense, as it almost always was when they were together like this, but they had a guest, Ariane was in the middle of cooking dinner, and Elster had chores to do around the house, so, they each sat back upright.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Also, not just my memories, yours too, apparently.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Huh.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane turned herself sideways on the bed to better face Elster. “She proved it to me by talking about things we did that no one would have been able to guess, like when we had that slumber party in the lower observation room, or when I showed you all of the paintings I had made of you.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster nodded as she listened to Ariane, sighing after she finished. “Well, um… what does she want?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane glanced toward the bedroom door for a moment before she shrugged her shoulders. “She said she just… wants to spend time with us.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster narrowed her eyes. “Really?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I don’t quite get it either,” Ariane said. “But, she sounds sincere… so, I agreed to let her stay and talk to you about it.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“How is she even… here?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane shrugged her shoulders. “I don’t really know, all she said was that she had been searching for us for a long time… and finally found out where we were.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster took a long breath. She found Ariane’s hand and held it again, eventually bringing her knuckles to her lips to kiss, which she smiled over. They both stood up in unison, and Elster hugged her. She sighed into her embrace, with each leaning on the other in perfect harmony.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I guess… I want to see more before I decide on anything,” Elster said quietly.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane leaned back and pecked her wife on the lips. “I understand, but, can I just say something?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster nodded.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane stepped back while holding Elster’s hands. She rubbed her thumbs over her knuckles and looked off to the side for a few seconds before she peered back into her eyes.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“In just the short time she and I talked… it felt so… liberating,” she confessed.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster cocked her head to the side as Ariane thought best about how to continue.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“As much as I love you, Ellie, and you’ll always be enough for me… it felt so good to have someone else who understands what we had to go through to get here… Isa… Erika… they only know what they went through, and my family knows nothing. So, in a way… it dawned on me that it sort of felt like it was still just us, alone, on the Penrose,” she explained. Ariane lifted Elster’s hands and took a step toward her as she finished. “But, not anymore. That’s why I… want to give her a chance… does that make sense?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster thought for a moment before she gave a short nod. “It does, yes.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Thank you.” Ariane lifted herself on her toes for a moment to kiss Elster again before the two made for the door. “That uh, took longer than I expected, I hope dinner is still okay,” she said as she opened the door.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;However, when Ariane checked the kitchen, she found the pots and pans she was using empty and stacked away next to the sink. They both reconverged at the dinner table, where they found that Falke had not only finished the meal Ariane had been cooking, but was plating the stir-fried noodles, vegetables, and beef for the two of them.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She heard the two approach and turned her head toward them, offering a short, awkward wave. “I hope this was acceptable, but, as I noticed you were occupied for a while, I took it upon myself to finish your dinner, lest it get cold from sitting off the stove for too long.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster and Ariane looked at each other for a moment. Ariane muttered an ‘Umm…’ while Elster cleared her throat.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Thank you, Falke,” she thanked.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke nodded. “I would hate to intrude, but, may I join you for this meal?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane blinked a few times and nodded. “Yeah, go ahead.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“You can get yourself a plate,” Elster added.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke smiled.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Dinner was almost entirely quiet. Elster talked for a while about a car she worked on for most of the day, and Ariane briefly brought up the web page she was commissioned to design, but otherwise, the three sat at the table and quietly ate, especially Falke, who did not utter a single word.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She also offered to take care of all the dishes after dinner, but Elster took a stand, saying she could handle it.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Eventually, they agreed to work together with Elster washing and Falke rinsing and drying, leaving Ariane alone for a few minutes to flip through her novel on an armchair in the living room. Meanwhile, back in the kitchen, and with the water running to obscure her voice, Elster started prodding Falke for answers.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“So, what do you want from us?” Elster asked as she passed Falke a plate.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The Replika continued to work expertly and efficiently as she answered back. “As I told Ariane, I desire nothing from you. I only wish to be in your presence.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“But, isn’t that asking something of us?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Not necessarily. For the longest time, I thought I was content to merely observe from a distance.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster froze for a moment. Falke picked up on her sudden discomfort and sighed.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“My sincere apologies. I failed to consider how awkward that admission would feel.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster also sighed as she continued scrubbing. “It’s fine.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I also feel I must apologise and amend my earlier statement. I simply did not wish to have you feel like I was intruding on your lives… but my desire to be in your and Ariane’s presence is a request, no matter how benign I try to make it sound.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“...I accept your apology.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Thank you, Elster.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She paused again after handing the last plate to Falke. “Tell me, if you have my memories, then do you… love Ariane?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke rinsed the plate and slotted it into the rack before she braced herself against the counter and sighed. “I… do not know. I have no frame of reference for what love is.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“But you want to be with her.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke looked at her palms. “My… something in me aches at every thought of her. Of you as well. I could not remove either of you from my thoughts even if I wished to.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“So… these are happy thoughts, then?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She turned and looked down at Elster and smiled. “Now that I am here, yes, they are.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster nodded and folded her arms as she looked up at the massively tall Replika. “So, now you want to… develop your own frame of reference?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke blinked and frowned slightly. “Is… would that be acceptable?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster took a quick breath and exhaled. She reached behind her head and undid her ponytail, scratching the back of her scalp as her hair came loose.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“My wife wants to give you a chance, so, I will too.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke nodded. “That is all I could ask for, thank you.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;As they went to join Ariane in the living room, she got up from her seat and shared a quick hug and kiss with Elster, the two sitting down on the couch soon after. However, Falke stood at the edge of the living room rubbing her hands together again. Eventually, Ariane noticed her apprehension and reached behind Elster to pat the empty side of the couch, beckoning her over. Falke slowly walked over to the empty half of the couch and slowly sat down, with the small, relative to her, size proving to be just as much of an issue as before. Her bicep briefly brushed up against Elster’s shoulder and she quickly leaned away, only for Elster to soon after lightly clear her throat to get her attention.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Everything is alright,” she said. “We are just sitting together.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;With that, Falke visibly relaxed a little, leaning into the back of the couch as Ariane channel-surfed to find something to watch.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Oh, Falke?” she called out as she worked the remote. “You said you came here straight from Leng. Do you have a place to stay here in Rotfront?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke frowned slightly and looked away from the two. “I… presently do not.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;All went silent for a moment, until Ariane gently nudged Elster in her arm, offering her a smile when she looked to check what she was trying to signal. When she did understand, she exhaled sharply and nodded.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Would you like to stay here the night?” Elster offered.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Oh… would you really…?” Falke slowly looked back at the two as Ariane added on.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“We don’t have an extra bedroom, but, you’re welcome to crash on the couch, or, I could pull out a blow-up mattress,” she paused to take in how big Falke was and hastily added, “or two!”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I do not require sleep,” Falke stated, drawing looks of confusion from the two as she continued explaining. “I am powered by two high-capacity hydrogen fuel cells which only need to be replenished once during my operational lifespan… a point at which I am currently nowhere near approaching. Sleep, or rather, extended minimal activity mode can still be beneficial to my production model for conducting internal repairs of self-correcting circuits, but, generally speaking, I can move about as I do currently nearly one hundred percent of the time and still perform at peak efficiency.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster raised an eyebrow at Falke. Ariane just looked even more confused.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke briefly covered her mouth as she groaned to herself. “Well, um, sleep is still good. I enjoy the chance to sleep. I have even… had what I believe are dreams… about…” She stopped herself upon noticing Elster’s inquisitive glance and shook her head. “I will take the blow-up mattress for the night if that is acceptable.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I can help you look for your own place tomorrow after work,” Elster said. “Ari and I have been looking to get a bigger place anyway, so, if we do, you could probably have this one,” she explained. She turned to Ariane and asked, “That’s okay with you, right?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane slowly nodded before returning her attention to channel surfing, and just a few flicks later, she gasped. “Ah! I love this movie! And we’re in luck, we’re still really close to the start!”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;And so, they sat and watched the movie into the night. Elster got up once to make popcorn and grab drinks during a short break in the programming, while Ariane also left briefly during the movie to use the bathroom. But, near the end, Elster noticed that Ariane had fallen asleep against her, and so gently adjusted her seating to give her more comfort. Falke also watched Ariane as she quietly snoozed against Elster’s shoulder, and when Elster turned to get a look at her, she saw Falke wiping away a tear from her cheek.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Both remained awkward in silence for a moment until Falke confessed. “She is… so peaceful when she is asleep…”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster paused for a moment before she slowly nodded. Falke wiped away another tear. Elster exhaled softly.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Why don’t you… could you carry her to bed? And I’ll get yours set up?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke slowly sat upright before nodding very very deliberately. She stood up, and Elster prepared to move herself to give her a good angle to pick Ariane up, but as it turned out, that was not necessary. Ariane began to float off the couch, the trio of gems on the Replika’s forehead glowing softly as she gently guided the sleeping Gestalt into her arms, taking great care to keep her head just as stable and supported the entire time. She was technically light for a Replika such as her, but the mental weight of having Ariane in her arms taxed her heavily, even if she was more than prepared to accept it. Once she had her, Falke nodded to the slightly awestruck Elster, who quickly followed her into the bedroom to search through the closet for their blow-ups after the shock of Falke demonstrating her powers passed.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;As she approached the bed, Falke’s forehead gems glowed once more as the covers flipped to the side, opening a spot for Ariane to be laid down. She pulled the covers back over her sleeping form slowly, tucking her in as Elster left the bedroom with the air pump and mattress bags. She watched Ariane sleep for a minute, and in a moment where she thought it was just the two of them, she carefully reached for Ariane’s forehead and tenderly brushed aside some of her locks as she silently mouthed, ‘Sleep well.’&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She turned to leave the bedroom and briefly flinched as she noticed that Elster had been watching her from the doorframe, but she did not give her any immediate reaction. She beckoned Falke out of the room and she followed, quietly closing the door behind her as the two returned to the living room.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Can I see your hand?” Elster quietly asked.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke nodded and presented her left hand to Elster, who grasped it underneath with her right as she glided her left hand overtop, the simple gold wedding band shimmering briefly in the light overhead.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I believe you,” Elster said, looking up at Falke.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Thank you,” Falke quietly choked back.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The mattresses were inflated and bedding laid over them, and when it was time to sleep, Falke and Elster shared a brief, understanding nod before the former Replika shut the lights off and joined her wife in the bedroom. She leaned over Ariane’s sleeping form and gently kissed her on the cheek, then found herself surprised when Ariane kissed back.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Hey,” she said sleepily.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster sat on the edge of the bed beside her as she pulled off her socks. “Good day?” she asked.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane rubbed her eyes with the heel of her hand. “Interesting,” she said, smiling and adding, “and good.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster stood up after getting her socks off and opened her belt, letting her pants drop to her ankles. She bounced into bed behind Ariane and kissed her on the back of her neck as she worked the buttons on her shirt with a spare hand. Ariane giggled under the attack and pulled her arm out from under the covers to wrap around Elster’s back.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“How tired are you?” Elster whispered, starting to peel her shirt off once the last button was free.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane yawned lightly but continued to smile. “Not that sleepy,” she said, emphasizing her point.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster slowly grinned back and Ariane pulled herself out from under the covers to climb over her, running her hands up her abs to squeeze her chest before she leaned over to kiss her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Meanwhile, Falke lay on her back under the blanket, her hands clasped together just below her chest. She smiled at nothing and no one as her bioresonance crystals dimmed. She felt like chastising herself for peeking, but in the end, she realized that whatever there was to see would be no different in nature from what she had already been given. She was content enough just to have a taste of what her experiences yearned for so much.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She closed her eyes and dreamt of a beach on Vineta, staring out into the sunset as gentle waves crashed against what should have been her feet.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;A fantasy for sure, but, if this could be real-&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Why not that?&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;…..&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane was the first to slip out of the bedroom in the morning, something that had become more and more common ever since Elster got better at sleeping in following the change. She carefully peeled Elster’s sleepy arm off her side and slipped out of bed, giving herself a quick stretch before she got dressed for the morning. She sleepily shuffled into the kitchen in a pair of fluffy, pink slippers and accompanying housecoat, eager to start the day with a strong, hot cup of coffee.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Only, as she smelled the air, the scent of fresh brewing was already present, and so many other delectable smells.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She tiptoed around the short corner toward the dinner table and felt a short burst of relief as she was reminded of Falke’s presence, being immediately confronted by their Replika guest pouring a trio of glasses full of what looked like orange juice. In addition, there was also a trio of placements set for breakfast: each plate had a slice of toast topped with scrambled eggs and some white shavings sprinkled on top, half of what looked like a lobster, and a small cup of coffee, each one of the three looking quite distinct.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Good morning,” Falke greeted her while her back was still turned to Ariane. Once she had finished pouring the orange juice, she picked up the cup of black coffee and turned around to present it to Ariane, getting down on one knee so she was at least a little closer to her height. “Cappuccino for you, I hope you enjoy it,” she said as Ariane took the warm cup.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She took a sniff of the coffee and admired the lily flower drawn into the milk foam atop the surface but stopped short of taking a sip. “Wait, we don’t have an espresso machine,” she pointed out.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke blinked and pointed toward the edge of the kitchen counter. “You do now.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane turned and saw a brand new espresso machine complete with a steam wand. “Huh, thank you,” she said before taking a sip of her coffee. “Oh, wow!” she exclaimed after tasting the frothy, sweet, warm beverage, pausing to take another quick sip. “Falke, this is incredible!”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The Replika smiled as she stood back up. “Breakfast is ready, also…” Falke trailed off as she peeked behind Ariane and leaned toward the living room. “Is Elster still asleep? I thought this was around the time the both of you were typically awake?” she asked.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“It used to be,” Ariane replied before taking another sip of coffee. “But lately she’s been getting… she’s gotten better at not getting up so early,” she explained, trying to force the accidental blush away from her cheeks.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke nodded. “Ah, I see…”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane put her cappuccino down on the dinner table. “I’ll go wake her up,” she said before walking back to the bedroom, unable to face Falke with how red her face was getting.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;While Ariane was gone, Falke looked over her breakfast presentation one last time. She hastily turned Elster’s plate seven degrees counter-clockwise so it was perfectly perpendicular to Ariane’s on the flank, and she dashed back to the kitchen to grab another small pinch of chopped chives for Ariane’s plate, sprinkling them atop her soft, scrambled eggs so each dish looked as exactly alike each other as they could.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane returned with an extremely sleepy-looking Elster not long after. She shuffled in behind Ariane with her hair an utterly frazzled mess, wearing a plain, button-down pyjama top and bottoms, rubbing an eye with the heel of one hand while she reached under her shirt and scratched her modestly muscular abdomen.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Here, Elster,” Falke called out as she pulled out her chair. Elster paused in front of the table for a moment before she sat down and got a good whiff of the meal Falke had prepared.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Holy hell… Falke, what is this?” she asked, lifting part of the lobster shell.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Soft scrambled eggs on fresh brioche with shaved white truffle, and grilled lobster with a garlic butter béchamel sauce,” she explained.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster stared at her plate in confusion for a moment, but Ariane picked up her eggs on toast and took a bite.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Oh my god-” Ariane quickly followed up with a second bite.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke sat down at her seat and watched as Elster continued to examine her meal. “The latte there is for you, as well,” she pointed out.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Oh,” Elster looked around and saw the coffee cup next to the glass of orange juice ahead of her plate. She picked it up and was about to take a sip, but stopped upon noticing that there was a bird drawn into the foam atop the latte. “Cute,” she remarked before taking a sip, raising the cup to Falke and giving her a nod afterwards.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Falke-” Ariane had to stop herself so she could bite a chunk of juicy lobster meat, “-the hell did you get all this?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I acquired it,” she answered, taking a sip of her doppio.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Yeah, but from where?” Ariane asked.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke shrugged her shoulders. “From the Gouverneurspalast.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane was in the middle of taking a sip of orange juice and almost spat out after hearing her. “You what?!”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Why?!” Elster barked.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke shifted her eyes between the two shocked women and sunk back slightly in her chair. “I just… wanted to make something nice… for you both…”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;An awkward silence followed for a few seconds, with only a relatively loud swallow from Ariane breaking the tension.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“This is… extremely sweet, but…” she started.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Let’s avoid potentially attracting any law enforcement attention in the future,” Elster finished.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke exhaled and nodded. “I understand… still, I am glad that the meal is agreeable.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“It’s delicious!” Ariane almost immediately praised. She waited for Elster to chime in but she was happily and quietly chowing down on her lobster, so she sneakily stubbed her in the shin with her toe underneath the table.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“O-Oh, yes, this…” She paused to swallow. “...Is honestly the most delicious meal I’ve ever eaten in my life,” she said, going right back afterwards to eating.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke smiled. She took another sip of her espresso before she started to dig into her egg toast with a knife and fork.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;One shower later after breakfast and Elster was off to work at her mechanic shop. The two had retreated to their bedroom to change, with Elster dressed back up in her full winter attire. The two shared a trio of kisses with Ariane before Elster left, both of them giggling between each one.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Anything you’d like me to pick up on the way home?” Elster asked.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane smiled and tugged down on the sides of Elster’s tuque so it was covering her ears. “No, I think we’re good. Just come home quick, love.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke sat on the couch reading a newspaper as the two lovers said their morning goodbyes. She tried not to peek too many times as the couple hugged and kissed, but each time she did, she felt the urge to rub her chest, as if something inside ached terribly. She heard Ariane sigh after the door clicked shut, and she quickly raised her newspaper over her eyes as she heard footsteps approach her in the living room.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Falke?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She slowly lowered the newspaper. Ariane stood across the coffee table in front of her in a pair of black stretch pants and a white crop top which left nothing to the imagining regarding her hips, thighs, and stomach being considerably softer than Falke’s borrowed memories pictured her having.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She lightly cleared her throat and kept moving her eyes up and down from her newspaper, not wanting Ariane to see her eyes lingering upon her plush curves, but not wanted her to think she was avoiding doing so either.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Can you help me move this? I need to lay out my exercise mat,” Ariane asked.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke looked at the coffee table. It was a small piece of furniture, she did not doubt that Ariane could easily have moved it herself, and she must have if this was a common routine done after Elster left for work in the morning. No, she wasn’t asking because she needed the help.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Like the other times she had done so since her arrival, Ariane just wanted her to feel included.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke closed the newspaper and smiled. She looked at the coffee table and it began to hover as her bioresonance crystals glowed. She moved it away from the living room space until Ariane gave her the okay, whereupon she gently set it back on the ground.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“That’s quite a handy power you have,” Ariane commented as she rolled out her mat.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke raised an eyebrow at Ariane. “But, you have it too, don’t you?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane stood silently on the mat.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“That is how you were… able to create this world for the two of you… why Elster is a Gestalt…”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane exhaled as she started her stretches, pulling one leg behind her into a backward lunge. “It was… but… I’ve since given it up.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke leaned forward on the couch as Ariane brought her leg back forward and swapped it with the other one. “Why…?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Why give it up?” Ariane repeated as she stood up and bent over to touch her toes.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“You could have had everything,” Falke stated. She scooted to the edge of the couch and slowly stood up. “With the power you must have possessed… why not make yourselves masters of the world? Of the universe? Why not have your every whim and need catered to? I do not mean this to be condescending… I simply fail to understand… why settle for…” Falke looked around the small, but cozy apartment and raised her hands. “This relative… mediocrity?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane got on her stomach and bent her upper body backward as far as she could, exhaling once she hit the peak. “Because… what I wanted… what Elster and I wanted… was a life…” She slowly returned to her resting position and took another short breath, exhaling sharply afterwards. “Not a heaven.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke nodded and sat back down. “So, is that why you are performing these exercises?” she asked, trying not to stare too hard at Ariane as she performed all sorts of stretches which seemed almost perfectly designed to show off all of her fantastic curves. “So you can experience all aspects of life? The good and the bad? The easy and the difficult? The exciting and the benign?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane turned her head to the side and flashed a toothy grin as she got on her hands and feet and stuck her behind as far upward as possible. “No, I do them because they make my butt look amazing,” she teased, winking at her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke coughed and immediately turned her gaze away, but Ariane chuckled and beckoned her back.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Hey, you can look, it’s fine.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She did so and saw Ariane sit with her feet under her rear as she stretched her chest.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“A girl likes to feel admired,” she stated, smiling as she looked forward. Falke chuckled just a little and continued to watch as Ariane kept going through her routine. She pulled a heel up her thigh to her crotch as she pressed her palms together over her head. “Actually though, I mostly like doing these stretches because they’re relaxing, and can help calm me down.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke nodded. “You still… carry the pain?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane looked toward her and nodded. “I didn’t want to give it up. Yes, it hurts, but.” She put her foot down and exhaled slowly. “What we went through made us who we are. If I got rid of that, would it really still be us anymore?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke looked away. She didn’t have an answer for her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Could you do me a favour? I left my water bottle by the sink, can you grab it for me?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She nodded and got up.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane also had a job, but she worked mostly from home as a digital graphic designer within the fast-growing computer revolution. She still took out her easel and paintbrushes on a regular occasion, but much of her artistic work was now done with a keyboard and mouse, and she relished every opportunity she had to do so.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Ariane…?” Falke asked as she bent over behind her, trying to get a better view of the picture she was composing. “Why is your monitor… turned on its side?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She rolled her chair to the side and showed off what she was making: a giant, digital burger with each of its various components suspended apart from each other.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I need the image to be taller than it is wide, and, so, this is the easiest way for me to do so,” Ariane explained. She also showed Falke how she held the mouse at a ninety-degree angle to account for the special orientation of the monitor. Falke in turn watched very carefully and quietly for several hours as Ariane finished and refined her image, with her getting up every half hour or so to do a quick stretch or get some more water. At one point, she winced upon stretching her back, doubling over and holding her side. Falke rushed forward and knelt next to her as she put a supportive hand on her shoulder.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I’m okay, Falke,” Ariane winced as she slowly stood upright.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“You still suffer from lower back complications?” Falke asked.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane looked toward her and nodded. “Working a desk job has its advantages and disadvantages…” She paused to try and stretch again, only to let out a quiet ‘ow’ and groan under her breath. “...This is one of the disadvantages.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke nodded. Ariane stood and stared at her for several increasingly uncomfortable seconds.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“...Falke?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Hmm?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“You can let go of my shoulder now.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke gasped as she snapped her hand back as if she had just touched a hot burner. She prepared an instinctual apology but stopped as Ariane smiled and chuckled.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Is something the matter?” she asked.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“No, nothing like that,” Ariane replied. Falke blinked at her, and Ariane started walking off toward the kitchen, with Falke catching up to her a few seconds later. Once at the fridge, Ariane paused before grabbing the handle and instead peered back at Falke over her shoulder. “It’s just that… back then, you reminded me a lot of Elster, early on.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I see,” Falke said, swallowing as Ariane turned back toward the fridge and opened the door, looking for something. She rubbed her hands together as Ariane stuck her head into the fridge, swallowing once more. “If I may suggest…” she trailed off to lightly clear her throat, “I could… give your back a massage… I do know exactly how they… helped you previously.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“You know.” Ariane peered over her shoulder again and smiled. “That’s not such a bad idea.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke also smiled back, but before she could suggest anything further, Ariane stuck her head back in the fridge and soon after groaned as she pulled a box out from the shelves within.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Ellie forgot her lunch… again!” Ariane griped as she turned around and set it on a nearby kitchen counter. She stared at the box silently for a few seconds before she sighed and opened the door to her bedroom. Falke didn’t go in after her but saw her start to riffle through the closet, eventually pulling out a pair of snow boots. She lightly cleared her throat to get her attention.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I could… deliver it to her?” she suggested after Ariane turned to look her way.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She smiled.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;…..&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Luckily, Elster’s mechanic shop was only a few blocks away from their apartment complex, but a few blocks away in the middle of a Rotfront winter would remain a struggle for all but the most seasoned pedestrians, but Falke didn’t let any of the snow or wind affect her as she trudged through the sidewalks which city workers fought a losing battle to keep clear. However, even in her jeans and jacket, Falke wouldn’t exactly remain inconspicuous if seen walking around the streets of Rotfront, especially given her Replika model’s frequent appearance in military propaganda, so Ariane bundled her up further, adding a scarf, gloves, ushanka, and a pair of boots tied around her stumps as extra insurance, as well as tying her into a ponytail she could tuck into the back of her jacket.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Still, being two and a half metres tall was bound to attract some amount of attention, and she caught a fair number of confused and bewildered stares from a few other Rotfronters during her walk, though, none stopped her for questioning, and she made it to Elster’s shop without any incident after just a few minutes of walking. A bell jingled on the door as she stepped inside, and she heard Elster shout from the workshop through the door to the front counter.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I’ll be there in a second!”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke tapped the lunch box in her hands as she waited for Elster to arrive, which she did just under twenty seconds later wearing a smudged pair of blue-gray coveralls and with her hair tied into a short ponytail.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Oh, Falke?” she said in surprise upon seeing her. “What are you doing here?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke held out the lunch box. “You forgot this.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster blinked a few times before she registered what she held in her hands. “Oh… Oh!” she gasped, then leapt forward to take it, popping the top open and throwing a piece of sushi into her mouth immediately. “Gods… been… starving… thank you!” she thanked between chews.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke followed Elster back into the workshop where they found a pair of chairs by a small table to sit down at. Elster put her bento on the table and kept popping bites of sushi, octopus hotdog, and gyoza into her mouth as they tried to share a conversation.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“So… did Ariane… ask you to… deliver this…?” Elster asked with her mouth very full and busy.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke cleared her throat lightly into her hand and smiled. “No, actually, I… offered to do so myself so she didn’t have to interrupt her day.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster paused for a few seconds. She swallowed and smiled.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Then… I’m glad you were there,” she said.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke smiled.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Listen,” Elster said, stopping once again to eat more of her lunch. “It’s been a super slow day… I’m not expecting more customers to show up… why don’t you stay and help me finish fixing up this car, and then we can surprise Ariane by making it home early?” she suggested.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Well, I think that is a lovely idea.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;With Falke’s help in passing her tools when Elster was underneath the vintage model and being able to watch the engine under the hood while she tried the ignition, gas, and brake pedals, the two finished their work on the car in just over an hour, leaving Elster whistling happily as she flipped the door sign to ‘Closed’ and locked the door behind them as they left, her lunch box tucked under an arm.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I know Ari asked me to come straight home, but, I still want to get her something,” Elster said as the two walked side by side down the street.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“What would you like to get her?” Falke asked.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I don’t know, just, something,” Elster said, adding after a moment of thought, “Flowers, maybe?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“May I make a suggestion?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Of course.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Do you have any cold or hot compresses at your apartment?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster stopped walking for a moment. “No… why do you ask?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke stopped beside her. “Ariane had some issues with back pain earlier.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster cocked her head to the side and raised an eyebrow. “She did?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke nodded. “For a while, it seems. She seemed to believe it was because of her desk job.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“...Why wouldn’t she tell me?” Elster asked, looking down at the ground between them.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Because it is Ariane,” Falke answered. “We both know how she is regarding personal issues.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster sighed and nodded before stretching a light smile across her lips. “I guess some things never change, huh.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Just then, something clicked inside Falke. She watched Elster’s expression throughout the reveal go from confused, to surprised, to sullen, before ending on a small, but warm smile. So, she smiled as well.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I think I understand, now,” Falke said aloud.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster stopped in her tracks again and raised an eyebrow at her, but Falke closed her eyes and lightly shook her head whilst growing her smile.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“It is nothing, just something I had a talk about with Ariane earlier,” Falke explained before the two resumed their walk. “We should proceed quickly, the sooner we get what we need and arrive home, the happier she will be.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster smiled and nodded.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;…..&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster shivered upon walking into the apartment lobby. She patted herself all over her body and arms, trying to shake off as much of the clingy snow as she could.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“At least we’re past the worst of it if we’re getting wet snow now,” she commented as they both stepped into the elevator.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;They had a fair number of floors to go, and the elevator was somewhat slow, so after a few seconds of awkward silence, Elster decided to strike up a new conversation.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Do you get cold?” she asked Falke.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The Replika turned and looked down at Elster. “Didn’t you?” she asked back.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster shrugged her shoulders. “I honestly have no idea, I don’t have a frame of reference for being cold,” she answered. “The Penrose was powered by a nuclear reactor, so, the ship was at least never cold, and the one time I had to go outside I did so in an AVA suit.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I see. I am not sure about the LSTR unit model, but, the FLKR model was not programmed to feel such hampering sensations as pain, which would include extreme heat and chill.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Hmm… I know my systems would have started to shut down rather quickly if subjected to sub-zero temperatures for prolonged periods… but I never knew if I could feel a chill… I suppose I’ll never know, now.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“...Does it bother you, abandoning your Replika body?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster hummed for a moment before she answered. “I won’t lie, there were a lot of things it was nice for… but… this feels much more…” she waved her hands down the length of her body, “...who I am… and there are many things I can only do with it.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“...Understandable for someone in your position.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“You know…” Elster trailed off as the elevator reached their floor and the two stepped off, “had Ariane been aware of your presence, I am sure she would have offered the same to you.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Hmm…” Falke hummed as they walked toward the door. “I am not sure… right now, I would stay who I am… but over time…”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;They reached the apartment door, but as Elster took out her keys and started fumbling with them, she cursed, “Ah, verdammt!”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke knelt next to her. “Is something wrong?” she asked.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster rolled her eyes as she sighed. “I forgot to check the mail! I’m expecting an important package any day now, I have to go check if it’s arrived.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She handed Falke her lunch box and the keys and told her to let herself in while she raced downstairs to check the mail room. So, Falke shrugged her shoulders and opened the door, calling out just loud enough to announce her presence.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Ariane…! We’re back!” She shut the door behind her and started taking off her winter fare, hanging her hat and scarf on the coat rack. “Elster’s just behind me, she just had to go check the mail!”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;No response. Falke scanned around the apartment from the door. She didn’t see Ariane in the kitchen or the living room, and after walking in further she didn’t see her at her desk.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;But, she heard whimpering. It came from the bedroom.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke quickly walked over to the bedroom door, leaving Elster’s lunchbox on the kitchen counter. The door was slightly ajar, and she could hear Ariane sobbing quietly through the crack. Part of her said it would be best to wait for Elster. She might know them intimately from sharing their memories, but they only barely knew her. What right did she have to even feel concern for her in this situation, let alone feel she had a right to offer support?&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Except, she was there, and Ariane was in distress.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster wouldn’t have hesitated. Neither could she.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke gently nudged the door open and slowly walked inside. Clothes were strewn around the floor in front of the bed, and Ariane sat naked at the head of the bed with her knees drawn close to her chest while she hugged a pillow against her upper torso. She either didn’t hear Falke enter the apartment or her bedroom, or didn’t bother to acknowledge her presence in any way. She only looked straight ahead, occasionally burying her eyes and face into her pillow. Falke cautiously approached the bed until she was as close to Ariane as she could get without getting onto it. She briefly reached out her hand, but quickly decided against giving any physical comfort, at least for now. Instead, she sat down on the edge of the bed and pushed herself back until she was sitting next to, but not touching Ariane.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I am just right here,” was all she said, just enough to make Ariane fully aware of her presence.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Then, she waited.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She rubbed her hands together, trying not to look too often at Ariane as she softly wept. Her mind went awash with theories over what had upset her, but she tried to keep her focus on the here and now. If Ariane wanted to tell her what had happened, she would, there was no point in speculating about it.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She suddenly felt something soft lean against her arm. She looked over and say Ariane had moved up next to her and was leaning her head against her bicep. She briefly flexed her arm, intending to wrap it around Ariane, but stopped herself to seek consent.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“May I?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane looked up at her with watery eyes and nodded.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke carefully wrapped one arm behind her back and another under her knees and gently lifted her into her lap. She sat her sideways so she could lean her head against her chest and simply stroked her hair for comfort as her sobs slowly dimmed.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“It’s stupid,” Ariane choked out, almost laughing into one of her sobs. “I shouldn’t be this fucking upset over it.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke wrapped her other arm around Ariane and held her just a little bit more snug. “Ariane, I…” She paused to swallow, unsure of what she intended to say would be received well, but knowing she had to say it regardless. “I know you well enough to know you would never be this upset over something… stupid.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“It is, though,” Ariane said, sighing afterward. “It’s not like things are over, we’ll just try again… but I can’t help…” She stopped as she started to break down again, and wrapped an arm around Falke’s back as she turned her face further into her chest. “Maybe this is what I deserve for… trying to steal valour.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Everything suddenly clicked into place in Falke’s head. Elster becoming a Gestalt was not the only change Ariane had made. They truly wanted a chance at everything they had been denied.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Listen,” Falke steeled herself to speak somewhat harshly. She didn’t want to, but felt it was necessary to get her intended point across. “I will not have any of that kind of talk. You deserve this. You have both more than earnest this chance, this happiness,” she said, pausing to take a breath. “This God grants you that,” she added.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane briefly chuckled, but otherwise remained silent. Falke took it as a good sign.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“You will be okay,” Falke spoke much more sweetly. She glanced up and saw Elster standing at the doorway to the bedroom with a shocked and concerned expression across her face. “We’ll both make sure of that.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster nodded and quickly pulled her boots off before climbing onto the bed. She got up next to Falke and reached over to rub Ariane’s head, who turned just enough to show her left eye to her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Hey, Els,” Ariane greeted her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster lowered her hand and rubbed Ariane’s back. “You alright?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane choked as she drew a breath. “I’m sorry,” she apologised. “I miscarried.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster took a slow, long breath. Falke felt Ariane start to whimper harder in her grasp, so, feeling the time was right, she let go of her, and let Ariane climb over into Elster’s embrace. Except, as she did so, she kept one arm wrapped around Falke’s midsection, hooking the other around Elster’s neck as she cried into her shoulder.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster stroked her hair. Falke rubbed her back.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“There’s nothing to apologise for,” Elster said.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“We’re here for you,” Falke added.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Eventually, the two gently coaxed Ariane out of bed and into a soft, warm bathrobe to lie on the couch in while Falke prepared her some hot cocoa. Meanwhile, Elster sat next to her wife and placed an order for pizza on the phone, so none of them had to worry about anything aside from comforting each other for the rest of the night.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Can you get stuffed crust, please?” Ariane quietly asked, her voice still weak and scratchy from her earlier crying.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster held her hand over the speaker as she answered. “Of course, sweetie.” She pulled it away to add, “and can we make both of those cheesy stuffed crust?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The three sat in the living room watching movies and eating pizza and drinking hot cocoa and pop late into the night. Ariane sat in Falke’s lap through most of it, who would use her bioresonance to float more slices of pizza to her lips so she didn’t have to strain herself trying to reach the coffee table.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Oh, Elster,” Falke eventually called out hours into the night. “The package, was it there?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Oh, right!” Elster immediately got off the couch and walked over to the front door, where Falke saw she had left a very large, wrapped package. She carried it back over to the couch and put it down on the ground in front of Ariane. “Just a… well, not really little, but, something for you,” she said.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane smiled lightly as she tore into the gift wrapping, gasping slightly as she pulled the paper and plastic wrapping away to reveal a giant, brown teddy bear with a red bow-tie.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Oh, this is adorable, Ellie!” she said, picking up the plushie and hugging it tight.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster rubbed the back of her head as she grinned. “I uh, got it for you because I know you sometimes miss having someone to hug while I’m away at work,” she explained, turning her attention to Falke after, who noticed and looked up at her. “But… perhaps you already do, now.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane put the teddy down so she could get up and share a hug and kiss with her wife, but after her kiss, she rested her head sideways on Elster’s shoulder so she could look back and smile at Falke.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She nodded and smiled back. Ariane’s smile was just as much for her as it was for Elster.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Not long after, Falke was charged once more with carrying a very sleepy, and now very full Ariane back to bed, which she did so with all the same care and tenderness she had before. She brushed the hair atop her forehead aside again, and lightly ran the back of her fingers across her soft cheek.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Sleep well,” she said aloud this time, then, with a small amount of trepidation, she quietly added, “I love you, Ariane.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Just before she stood up to walk away she saw a smile form across Ariane’s supposedly sleeping face, and she sighed happily as she turned off the lights and left the bedroom.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Back in the living room, Elster had finished setting up Falke’s bed again, and she stood by it with one arm wrapped in front of her chest while her other hand pinched her chin.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Sorry to continue to intrude on you like this,” Falke apologised in advance as she approached her. “I know we did not get a chance to look for housing today, but, I feel conflicted over continuing to occupy your space like this.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster didn’t look Falke’s way for a few seconds. When she did, she sighed peacefully and smiled up at the massive Replika.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“No need to apologise, Falke,” she said. “I understand if you would like to seek out a place to call your own… and we still need to upgrade our own dwelling… but… please, I don’t think either of us would mind if you stayed as long as you wanted.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Thank you,” Falke thanked. She started to walk toward her bed, expecting the day to finally be coming to a close, but Elster called out to her one last time.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Falke?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She turned toward her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster swallowed loudly. “Could you… come down here for a moment?” she asked.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke nodded and got down on one knee so her head was only modestly higher. Elster closed the distance between them, and without much forethought or fanfare, reached up through her long hair to the back of her head, pulling her the last bit closer to kiss her briefly, but tenderly on her lips.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;As she pulled her lips away, Elster saw a pair of tears stream down Falke’s cheeks, even as she did her best to remain as calm and stoic as possible. She reached up with her thumb and wiped away the two droplets before wrapping her arms around Falke and giving her a gentle hug as she patted her back.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Thank you,” Elster whispered to her, almost starting to choke up herself as she sighed once more. “I’m glad you’re here,” she said.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;After that, Falke briefly returned the hug, rubbing Elster’s back for a few seconds before she pulled away and smiled at her, leaving soon after to join Ariane in bed.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke took one last look around the apartment before she decided to settle in under her covers.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She never had a word for home before, but she knew what it was now.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She had never known love, but she had it now.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Maybe, eventually, she could learn what family meant also.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She closed her eyes and dreamed.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The three of them laid out on a sunny beach atop soft towels. Ariane laid with her back to the sun, trying to pick up a bit of colour, Elster sipped on a cool drink as she watched the waves, Falke stuck her feet in the sand and wiggled her toes, enjoying the foreign but strangely satisfying feeling of the warm sand wrapped around her skin. Their two kids played down closer to the water. They constructed a brilliant sand castle, calling back multiple times for ‘mom, momma, and ma’ to take a look and congratulate their progress. Eventually, Elster got up to join them, the three of them laughing as they added more and more to their growing sand fortress. Ariane called out to Falke, asking her to spread a little more lotion on her back, which she did so gently and carefully, admiring the soft hums Ariane made as she massaged the lotion into her back and rear.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She dreamed harder.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Out deeper into the ocean were Isa and Erika, the former driving a speed boat with Erika wakeboarding behind her. Their laughs made it all the way to shore even through the noise of the waves and motor. Closer to shore but still in the water were her cadre of beautiful hummingbirds. The six of them worked in tandem bouncing a large, colourful beach ball between themselves. One of them briefly looked toward the beach and gave Falke a quick wave, which she happily returned. Off to the side of them on the beach was a small, self-built barstand where her Adler stood at attention, mixing drinks on queue and delivering refreshments when asked. He walked by with a tray in his hand and handed Falke a champagne cocktail. She raised the drink to him and smiled, with Adler smiling back just as warmly.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She dreamed harder.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Out along the line where the water met the beach walked a pair of tan, brown-haired women in colourful, flowing sundresses hand-in-hand. They looked without a single care in the world, and took each other for a playful dance atop the wet sand as water splashed about their feet. Elster and Adler worked together to set up a grand barbecue as the sun started to make its initial dip. They cooked up a smorgasbord of fish, sausages, burgers, and prawns, creating a feast that lasted well into the orange and purple hues of the Vinetan sunset. When night started to come, Falke led the kids inside for bedtime, but not before giving each of them a quick ride atop her shoulders on the walk back to their beachside house, providing a view to them of the wondrous blue ocean that would never be matched. She read them each a bedtime story before tucking the two in, and was soon joined in the master bedroom by her two wives.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She dreamed harder.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She started to unbutton her shirt, but Elster sneakily and playfully shoved her back onto the bed, letting Ariane straddle her hips before she could get back up. Ariane kissed her from her forehead down her cheeks, nose, lips, chin, and neck down to her chest as she finished undoing her shirt, and Elster climbed in behind her to pull it down her arms before the three shared a warm, fierce hug atop the bed. By the end, the three lay bare together atop the sheets, Ariane sandwiched between the two other women in Falke’s lap as she and Elster explored her wonderful body with their hands and lips. They turned and twisted amongst themselves into uncountable positions before ending in a simple, but tender spooning embrace. Elster held Ariane in front of her while Falke wrapped her arms and legs around them both from behind.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;They smiled, and they dreamed.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Regardless of whether it was a waking dream, or a sleeping truth, it was real to her, and it was real to all of them.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;They just had to build it themselves.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div id="feedback" class="feedback"&gt; &lt;h3 class="landmark heading"&gt;Actions&lt;/h3&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
