      <title>Villainous</title>
      <link>https://www.scribblehub.com/series/1102864/villainous/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">fb38b3f1a3ef2fbae43cd8f96700e86e77322f99</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 18 Jun 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Life has been amazing for Celeste ever since her powers emerged, thrusting her into a new life of superhero adventures! She gained the body of her dreams, freedom from her terrible foster home and her favourite superhero has become her trusted mentor.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Everything was perfect until a climactic battle concluded with her broken, humiliated and her secret identity exposed to her triumphant nemesis. She is now faced with a strange deal, her foe offering an end to their vicious rivalry and only asking for one thing in return.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Celeste will be adopted by her foe, supported all the way along her transition and spend her life loved and adored.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Cynthia Sable is the enigmatic CEO of Sable Inc. by day and the feared supervillain Entropy by night. Encased in her alien power armour she rules the criminal underworld with an iron fist.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She has spent her entire life running, running from the knowledge that everything was wrong, that this isn't the life she's supposed to live. that she could be something better, something heroic.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;When she takes in a strange teenager with mysterious ties to her long-forgotten past, she's forced to reconcile with who she is and what she could become.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Updates Wednesdays.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;The Sensational Solari! Part 1&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;It’s a warm Friday afternoon in Utopia and Celeste is bored out of her mind. Mrs. Callaghan stands in front of the class excitedly rambling about the themes of some old play to half asleep students staring absentmindedly at the slowly ticking clock, counting down the moments until they’re finally thrust into the weekend, all except for a thin figure leaning towards the window, she brushes her hand against a strand of thick unwashed hair and tucks it behind her ear. The class would also be mind numbingly boring for Celeste, if it wasn’t for the talking Tyrannosaurus Rex rampaging right outside the window, surrounded by an army of dinosaurs.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Lazer beams and machine gun fire ricochet through the street, its entire foundation shakes as a car shatters against the wall, caught just in time by the school’s force field. Not a single person pays attention to the ongoing carnage, not even a quick curious peek. Except for Celeste, she leans closer towards the window, utterly awestruck by the chaos below.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;This is the second time this week that Doctor Dinosaur has dared attack Utopia City with his army of cyborg prehistoric monsters. The school’s shields should hold on until a nearby hero team defeats the diabolical mad scientist, but it’s still unbelievably exciting. The girl continues to stare out the window, watching as a triceratops fires its laser mounted gatling gun at a small woman in a brown and black bodysuit covered in totems and technology. Scavenger leaps towards her foe, razor sharp claws unfurl from her gauntlets, she shoots out a grappling hook towards a nearby building, swinging high in the sky and elegantly landing on the monster’s back. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The creature roars as it tries to throw the woman off. She holds on tight as the dinosaur charges down the street, away from view shrieking and hollering. A sleek robot floats above the battle, his clear fishbowl helmet showing a purple brain pulsing with psionic energy, psychic tendrils surround him, swatting at a swarm of fierce pterodactyls swarming him.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;A lone T-rex, a small pair of glasses affixed to his nose, Dr Dinosaur is unsurprisingly a talking dinosaur. No one quite knows how he got his powers but it’s rumoured that he’s still a human, just stuck in an overly elaborate fursuit. He begins to lecture the excited crowd stuck behind police barricades about his grand evil plan, but his speech is blocked by the glass. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The crowd suddenly hushes when they notice a broad woman in a billowing green cape pushing past them. she hops over the barricade and saunters towards the monster with a confident swagger, as if she has already won the battle before it's begun. The crowd is utterly starstruck, their eyes focused on The Changeling: the most powerful sorceress on earth, leader of the paragons and of course, the coolest superhero alive! &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Groups of excited fans surround the barricades waving signs of their favourite heroes, hooting and hollering. Changeling waves at them, her sharp teeth shining like jewels in the sunlight, her cropped green hair lightly blowing in the early summer wind. With a quick flourish she undoes her cape, hexes and runes surround her hands while she recites a spell under her breath, a glowing emerald energy engulfs her, breaking into thorns and moss, large flower covered wings sprout from her back covering the onlookers behind her.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Changeling shouts something at Dr Dinosaur, causing him to blush with embarrassment, no doubt some ill timed quips or intelligent insults. The crowd is engulfed with laughter only worsening the monster's anger. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Dr Dinosaur charges at Changeling, roaring with rage. Changeling lets out a mighty yell as she soars her foe, her moss covered knuckles contort into thin sharp spikes, she readies her fist and lets out a mighty yell as it connects with the scientist's jaw, shattering his cybernetic enhancements.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Jason!” a voice yells from across the classroom dragging Celeste back into reality. The name hits Celeste like a kick to the guts. The girl turns to see her entire class staring at her, and Mrs. Callaghn standing above her. Her classmates snicker as Mrs Callaghan shakes her head. ”I asked you a question, young man.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Oh yeah! Of course.” The girl nods in response. “Could you repeat it?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“What is Mario’s key flaw in chapter four?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“His selfishness!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Mr Ash, there is no one named Mario in this play. '' Mrs. Callaghn frowns as the class bursts into laughter. The woman pulls down the blinds just as Changeling kicks Dr Dinosaur in his robotic balls.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Oh come on,” Celeste mutters under her breath.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Now, class, proceed to scene five. Jason, please stay after class.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The rest of the period stretches on for ages. Celeste tries to busy herself by fantasising about new additions to her costume and ruminations on various cases she's investigating. but it still isn't enough. By the time the bell rings it feels like five hundred years have passed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Celeste quickly throws her bag over her shoulder and tries to merge into the crowd ready for a weekend of excitement and adventure, but is stopped by a hand pressed against her shoulder.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I really hope you weren't trying to leave.” Mrs. Callaghn sternly stares at Celeste before leading her back inside the classroom. She sits down at her desk and opens one of her drawers, pulling out a large folder. She takes out a handful of sheets and places them on the desk. They are a collection of Celeste’s assignments, ranging from her first year of secondary school up until now. Her papers are all graded A+ but quickly decline after the date she gained her powers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Honey, what’s going on?” the teacher asks, pitifully smiling. “Jason, we both know you’re a smart young man. That poem you sent last year? Just, wow! But now it seems like you’re not even trying.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Look, it's just hard at home, ok?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“You know we offer lots of after school clubs and tutoring? I know your current circumstances are difficult, but you owe it to others not to waste that mind of yours.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I don’t know. I'll think about it, ok?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“You didn't hear this from me, but the school board has been talking a lot about you. If you miss even one more day, you WILL be expelled.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Yeah, fine.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Jason!” the teacher yells as Celeste storms outside.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Celeste shakes her head as she charges outside. Why should she need to worry about her grades when she can turn men to ash with a wave of her hand. why would she ever need to worry about her future when it’s already chosen for her.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She’s going to be a hero. The best of them. She’ll have her own spot on The Paragons, her face on billboards, and legions of fans. She is going to go down in history, and everyone who’s hurt her will be nothing but a footnote in her own biography.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;But for now, she just needs to survive high school.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Celeste pushes past hordes of excited teenagers discussing their weekend plans, through an empty broom closet, and straight into an alley behind the school.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She looks around carefully to make sure the alleyway is empty. her body is brimming with excitement as she ruffles through her school bag and begins removing her clothes. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She takes off her dirty jeans and baggy hoodie to reveal a pair of golden leggings and a white tank top with a simple star stitched onto its centre. With a flourish she takes a gold sequined cape from her bag and ties it around herself. Her uniform is a far cry from her predecessor's advanced power armour, but it will have to do for now. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Celeste takes a deep breath and reaches towards the sky. A flash of thunder roars in the cloudless sky, and in an instant she is covered by a golden aura, the veins beneath her skin glowing white. The light fills every cell within her body and begins to twist and transform her. She grows, shrinks, and contorts. Within a matter of seconds the facade named ‘Jason Ash’ disappears, revealing a tall cat-like creature with golden yellow fur and long encircling horns. Her stretchy clothes naturally settle as her long tail gently nests in a hole at the back of her leggings, swishing with excitement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Celeste discovered her destiny over a year ago, but she’s still amazed every time she transforms. Her human senses are so unbelievably weak compared to this, it’s as if she’s stumbling around blindfolded and deafened only for her restraints to be dramatically torn away. For a moment she can hear everything going on within the city, feel everything they feel, and see more colours than the human mind could even conceive of. Thankfully, she quickly regains control of her senses and tones them down to a reasonable level.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She releases the breath she was holding and flings herself into the sky, revelling in the cold air brushing against her fur. She’s always slightly terrified when she begins to fall, until instinct kicks in and she begins to hover.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Jason Ash is gone (Good riddance!), and in his place floats Solari, the last luminari and Utopia’s newest teen hero. Her career has been tumultuous to say the least, but whether it's been stopping car thieves or battling giant robots, she's done it with a smile on her face.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She takes a moment to admire the sprawling city below her and enjoy the cold air brushing against her fur. Being up this high and so close to the sun is utterly relaxing; it’s like a warm nap by the fireplace in the middle of the winter. She lies back and listens to the sounds and emotions of the city beneath her, tuning out all the negativity for just a few minutes. She smells a dozen hot dog stands, feels the joy of a man getting his wallet returned, and the satisfaction of the delinquent who found it upon getting his reward. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Everything is connected, everyone and everything. The universe is so big, and we’re all so alone. She just wishes everyone could understand that, feel what she feels for just a moment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Sadly, this respite is interrupted by a buzzing in Celeste’s ear. She presses it and a stern, husky voice echoes through.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Friday already! Good day at school?” Changeling’s voice fizzles through the headset; or, as Celeste knows her, Aoife. It’s been strange having your childhood hero constantly checking in on you and sending absolutely terrible memes. Six months ago Celeste utterly fucked up and attacked someone she really shouldnt have. She wouldn't even be alive now if Changeling hadn't suddenly intervened. Ever since, she’s been insistent on training her. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Of course not! Does it even matt–”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“You failed your English essay, didnt you?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Why does an alien princess need to learn about dead poets?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Well, what use is it in having a massive brain if you can't use it correctly?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Whatever. You’re not my mom y’know, it’s not even any of your business.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Well, you are my sidekick…”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Am not!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Not with those grades you’re not,” the woman on the other end chuckles. “Anyway, are you coming to the memorial? I know you hate speeches as much as I do, I was thinking we just grab a bite to eat and we watch? I could even tell you a few stories about her. Y’know, if you wanted to? But no pressure.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Oh. I’d like that.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Great! I’ll be at that cafe on Siegel and Shuster in ten.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;–&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Celeste can barely make out Memorial Park from the cafe. Crowds of mourners have arrived at the party for the grand ceremony. The glowing luminari shroom flowers are blotted out, and ignorant mourners stand on glowing solar flowers, the last of their kind. They’re far too resistant to be affected, but she still can't help but find it a bit disrespectful. Plants may not be sentient, but they still feel pain.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;A shining marble statue stands at the centre of the park, towering over everyone. Every detail is impeccably perfect from the soft fur covering her skin, her signature flowing braided mane that looks almost as if you could touch it, and her armour that is etched with every single gem, rune, and fine detail.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The statue rises above the mortals below her, staff in hand pointed towards the sky. A holographic display floats above her almost like a halo. It reads “Solari: 1989-2009. A princess to her planet, a saviour to us.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Yes, technically Celeste may have stolen her mantle from a long dead heroine. But it isn't like she was using it! The first Solari was, without a doubt, the greatest hero of her generation, arguably the best of all time. She saved the world more times than anyone could count, punched gods in the face, all the while juggling an extravagant entertainment career. Before she arrived aliens were just figures of derision and hatred, only fit to protect the city from other, more aggressive ‘freaks’. But she changed it all, she showed everyone how truly heroic they could be, how charismatic and stunningly beautiful. Even now, Celeste can't quite figure out how she got her horns to shine that way; no matter what product she uses, her own remain dull and lifeless.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She was Celeste’s idol throughout her entire childhood. Her entire room was, and still is, covered in whatever Solari merchandise she could scavenge. Celeste couldn't quite understand why she enjoyed watching this strange alien woman for hours on end, why she made her feel so loved, so seen!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Then one day Celeste’s powers emerged, and it all made sense. She wasn't just a mere human boy; she was better, faster, stronger, and infinitely more stunning. At last, all she knew was confirmed. She wasn't Jason Ash. She was Celeste, the last luminari!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Sure, she might have no idea where she came from: There was no crashed spaceship in her shed, no shadowy mentor dumping exposition and no long letter declaring her to be the result of some mysterious affair. But does it really matter? She doesn't need to be protected or comforted, but these people do.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;A group of assistants run around the stage, giving final touches to the lighting, sound equipment, and decorations. In mere minutes the festivities will begin. Citizens and heroes alike will take to the stage to honour their greatest hero. Aoife had backed out many years ago claiming to have “run out of the stories she’s allowed to tell”, and Celeste has none of her own. So they sit at this cozy cafe; Aoife with her overpriced latte and Celeste with a giant burger, chips, and milkshake. She wanted to refuse, but there hasn't been food at home in weeks and her lunch card ran out today.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Aoife sits in front of her, her cropped green hair is being gently blown by the late night wind.. The leader of the Paragons is a far cry from how she looked in her prime. Her temples are beginning to grey and new lines are being etched into her face by the day, her classic tight leo-tard and cape have been replaced by light fae-leather body armour, with strange runes etched in vulnerable spots providing protection and boosting her agility. A large faded scar covers her left eye, 4 cat like slashes, her irises snow white with swirls of green and gold floating around each other.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Her face is worn from decades of war but her smile is still as bright.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Aoife snickers when Celeste moves to cover her fries in sugar and sprinkles. Celeste groans in response. “What?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“She used to do the exact same thing.” Aoife smiles, watching as Celeste dips her sugary mess into her drink.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Yeah, we have weird taste buds. We’re aliens!” Celeste rolls her eyes mumbling through large mouthfuls. She was hungrier than she thought!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“You should mix some peanut butter in it sometime. C… Solari used to really like it.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Celeste averts her gaze and silently groans under her breath. Every time they hang out Aoife just has to go on a big rant about her dead girlfriend (although she’d never admit that to the press). Endlessly talking about just how similar Celeste is to her, from their looks to personality. Inevitably leading into a long lecture about some old mission they went on.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She sees a group of employees covered head to toe in black dragging a series of large boxes behind the statue and up around its scaffolding. Celeste shrugs and goes back to her fries, half listening to Aoife talking about the time they got stranded on an alien planet together.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;By the time Celeste has finished her fries, the ceremony is about to begin. Aoife begins to shift her posture, her tone growing low and serious. She reaches out and grasps Celeste’s hand.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Y’know, she would've been proud of you right? You’re doing a great job carrying on her legacy.” Aoife smiles, her eyes glittering with an emotion Celeste can't quite place. “Especially with what your home life is like… You get that I'd help you with anything, right? We’re partners.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I know.” Celeste tries to subtly shift her hand away, but it’s impossible without Aoife noticing. She feels hints of Aoifes emotions flow into her. There's pangs of affection, sadness, and worry. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“You look tired.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Didn't sleep much. Been busy with hero stuff.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Oh, baby.” Aoife sighs and then the worst feeling of all surges into her; pity, oh that fucking pity. All Aoife ever feels for her is that stinking pity! She tilts her head and begins to look at Celeste like she's some sick dog. “I had to move apartments after Entropy’s last attack. My new one is really cool! It has tons of spare bedrooms, and even a pool.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Celeste isn't an idiot. She knows what she's asking her, what she wants to do, but she can't. Aoife’s nice, but she’s busy, she doesn't need a dirty teenager taking over her space. She’s doing just fine on her own! &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Good for you.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“If you ever need a safe place–”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I get it!” Celeste snaps. “Look, tonight isn't about me or my problems, it’s about her! Let's just focus on the ceremony.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I suppose,” Aoife shrugs.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The memorial service is pretty typical. Some old Paragon-adjacent heroes come up desperate to relive their glory days in some form (or at least get back on television), and city council officials shamelessly exploit Solari’s image for votes. Celeste has already returned to her dinner, only half-listening, when the explosion happers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;A nameless reality show star moves to cut the large ribbon, officially unveiling the new Solari statue to the city, but the instant he does the boxes scattered across the stage begin to explode. The fast reflexes of Shieldbearer protects the participants on the stage from the worst of the blasts, but the music systems begin to shift from soft classic to screeching rock.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The smoke and dust from the explosion reaches up into the sky and inside it hundreds of red lights begin to glow, gently flying down to the ground. The smoke dissipates to reveal a figure in pitch black power armour, marked with large curved horns and glowing red lines stretching across her suit; behind her stands an army of robotic drones.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The crowd shrieks in fear as they start to recognise the figure above them. It’s none other than Entropy, or Cynthia Sable. The richest woman on the planet, queen of the super-villains, and the most dangerous woman alive.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Entropy first revealed herself to the world fifteen years ago, clad in a sleek alien power suit, holding Solari’s staff in her hands. She claimed to have destroyed her in single combat and had come to the city to reveal the corruption and weakness of their “so-called heroes.” Now, a decade later, she’s conquered the criminal underworld, and world economy. No one quite understands her “grand plan”, or even her most basic motivations.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;But Celeste knows what drives her. It’s nothing but pure jealousy: superpowers are the one thing money can't buy.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Celeste grits her teeth as she watches her nemesis stand on top of the rubble. Sunbird, a young avian-like hero, moves to slash at her with his sharp talons, but she grabs his wrist and shatters it. He falls to the ground, writhing in pain. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Pathetic. Now, in case any of you other attention seekers have any ideas.” Entropy snaps her fingers and her drones turn their guns towards the frightened crowd. “If any of you so much as move a muscle, your pathetic admirers will be reduced to ash. Do I make myself clear?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The politicians and heroes surrounding her bow their heads in defeat. “Good!” she chuckles. A drone appears behind her projecting a holographic screen, and two drones force the news crew to focus their cameras straight on it. “I hope you’re all comfortable, as I have some very interesting ‘tea’ about your favourite heroes here.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Entropy picks up the writhing Sunbird by his collar and presents him to the crowd. “Precious little songbird, you’ve fought an awful lot of popular villains in your short career haven't you? I wonder why that might be.'' The screen shifts to camera footage of Songbird in civilian guise meeting several villains behind a bar, handing them a trash bag of cash. It then shifts to him fighting the very same villains in the middle of memorial park the next day. They all fall without a single punch hitting them.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Do you have anything to say to your precious fans?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Don't believe her!” a balding fat man stands up from his seat. “How can we believe her! She calls herself the QUEEN of villains, for christ sakes!” The man is Simon Simeonson, former team paragon doctor and now Utopia Island’s minister for health.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“So eager! I was just about to get to you.” Entropy laughs as the screen begins to show the doctor speaking to the press, claiming funding for the ‘superhuman collateral damage fund’ has run dry, before cutting to a large bank account and financial documents showing large transfers of money from that very fund into his own personal account. A recording plays of him making a grand speech about metahuman rights and how they deserve to be treated just the same as regular citizens, then cuts to him profusely arguing for the sale of metahuman organs. “They’re villains, no one will miss them! Our donors could put their assets to much better use.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The doctor freezes, his jaw agape with horror. “It’s you. It’s always been you.”  Entropy’s hand closes around his throat, his face turning light purple. She pauses for a moment revelling in this man’s agony before turning to face the public.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Celeste can't help but roll her eyes, Entropy pulls this crap every few months, she’ll take a break from some big scheme to cause chaos and make a bunch of defamatory claims about well meaning heroes and civilians before vanishing. Sure, some allegations are true and the hero ends up in court or a politician gets fired but most of the time nothing changes. If these people  were actually doing such heinous attacks then the Paragons would step in to stop them, it's literally their job!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Now, I'm sure you’re all excited to see what I have to say about the rest of you all, but unfortunately I'm a busy woman so it should all be dropped online in about a half hour.” She casually tightens her grip around the doctor's throat, sending a loud crack throughout the area as Entropy tosses him to the ground like trash. The audience bursts into terrified screams,Songbird moves to stand but is pushed back into his seat by his manager.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Oh! Don't worry, you’re all safe.” The screen shifts to display Celeste herself, faded images taken from paparazzi depicting her assisting at a local soup kitchen. Entropy looks directly at Celeste. “If the freak claiming to be the so-called “new Solari’ faces me, right this instant, then I’ll let all of you go with a complimentary Sablebook Pro™.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Don't do it!” Aoife whispers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“But I've beat her before!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Barely! It's a trap! Focus on rescuing the civilians, I'll handle this.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I can't, she said it has to be me!”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Entropy chuckles as Celeste remains frozen in indecision. “Typical. A coward, just like your–”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She clenches her fists and begins to glow. Entropy wants a fight? Well, she's happy to give her one!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Celeste throws herself out of her seat and flings herself past the crowd into battle. She stumbles past the flying drones, past the bolts of magical energies and laser beams. Her fist is pointed in front of her, ready to deliver an overwhelming blow.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div class="wi_authornotes"&gt; &lt;div&gt; &lt;div class="p-avatar-wrap"&gt;&lt;a class="avatar has-link" href="/profile/80004/spillthekatea/"&gt;&lt;img id="acc_ava_change profile" alt="" src="https://cdn.scribblehub.com/avatar/s/20/ava_80004_1716946787.jpg"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="an_username"&gt;&lt;a href="/profile/80004/spillthekatea/"&gt;Spillthekatea&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div style="clear: both;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="wi_authornotes_body"&gt;  Thanks for reading! I would like to thank everyone who has helped me with this novel over the last year! especially my amazing editors and beta readers. There is another chapter already available which i hope you will enjoy! Chapters should hopefully be up on a weekly basis!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Comments are highly appreciated and if you'd like to share your thoughts directly i am @SpilltheKatea on twitter and &lt;a href="https://discord.gg/sDTGcvhgKj" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"&gt;i have a small discord here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
