      <title>From the Outer</title>
      <link>https://www.scribblehub.com/series/1099400/from-the-outer/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">a6213a45baba83519580e8f0bad4c4c815f82962</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 29 Jun 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Over a century after Sol's star turned green for but a moment, Earth and it's inhabitants have changed dramatically from their previous iteration. Humans were no longer mundane as instead each and every person was born with an ability ranging from minor telekinesis to taking the form of a gigantic dragon. Governments fell and rebuilt, countries were unrecognizable, and yet society continued to stand. Standards, Hybrids, and Star class individuals now prowled the globe in pursuit of their own goals, be that a career job or heroism. And of course, villains took to the stage as well.&lt;br /&gt; Here in New New York City, the people of this world were not creative with names, one Standard will face challenges of personal and national import. How will they handle their new life... of school and friendship? With a minor amount of danger tossed in for spice.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;--&lt;br /&gt; What to expect:&lt;br /&gt; Demi-humans, fluffy family activities, heroes of a grand scale and villains of the same, and the school life of a highschooler who loves and wishes to be loved right back.&lt;br /&gt; --&lt;br /&gt; Cover art was commissioned from- Albsans on Fiverr.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;Glossary Chapter&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;General Information: Subject to change&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;hr /&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Current classes of humans:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Standard&lt;/strong&gt;: Visibly identical to normal humans with the exception of hair and eye color. Each Standard posses an ability.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hybrid&lt;/strong&gt;: Visibly humanoid unless of the subclass [Hidden] where members can fold their inhuman additions into an extradimensional space. These include but are not limited to the following list;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Catia(Cat-folk), Foxia(Fox-folk), Alvine(Bird-folk), Cania(Dog and wolf-folk), Drago(Dragon and lizard-folk), Draydi(Dryad and plant-folk such as Alraunes), Bovadi(Cow and bull-folk), Ovadi(Sheep, ram, and goat-folk), Bun(Rabbit, bunny, and hare-folk), Slosia(Sloth-folk), Serpentia(Snake-folk), Mermandi(Fish, shark, whale, and dolphin-folk), Crusandi(Crustacean-folk), Cephalandi(Squid, octopus, and eel-folk), Vampitia(Bat-folk), Arachnia(Arachnid-folk), and Insectia(Insect-folk).&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Eels aren't a cephalopod, but I thought it would be funny to put them in with the squid and octopus people.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Star&lt;/strong&gt;: Can be either Standard or Hybrid in appearance as well as entirely unique with the class having four sub classes. Most Star-class individuals are capable of shapeshifting into their Star form and back;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Demigod, appears as a standard.  Legendary, appears as a legendary being with an example being the thunderbird. Mythological, appears as a mythological being an example being a phoenix. Finally, Deus, which appears as a named divine being with an example being Quetzalcoatl. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;hr /&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Notable Places and Political Entities:&lt;/strong&gt; New States of America, Free Kingdom (United Kingdom), Chixian Shenzhou (China reverted to a previous name after going through a major reformation and entering a new feudal period), Japan, the Endless North (The remnants of Russia), and the Independent Hybrid Tribes.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Common Settings&lt;/strong&gt;: The Quad-Tree System, the Heroes Union HQ, Pleasant View Plaza, Moonlight Square, Pinnacle Plaza, The Grand Harbor, The Lunaris (Lily's apartment), Catori Arena, and the Grand Arena.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;hr /&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Class schedule for student Lily Salem: Maplewood high, first year:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Ms. Linne Blank: Math (Algebra two) (Monday, wednesday, friday 8-10) &lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Mr. Jake Drus: Social studies (Monday, wednesday, friday 10-11) (History first, then civics, then economics, then etiquette, then random)&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Lunch: 11-12 &lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Ms. Flo Hall: History (Monday wednesday, friday 12-2) &lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Ms. Amaya Sansa: Languages (Monday wednesday friday 2-3:30)&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Lena Salora: Hybrid Studies(Tuesday and Thursday 8-10)&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Ms. Aileen Vanguard: PE (Female)(Tuesday and thursday 10-11)&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Lunch 11-12&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Ms. Alessia Belay: Combat/Self Defense (female)(12-2)&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;General teachers: Free time (Tuesday and thursday 2-3:30)&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;hr /&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Common Characters:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lily Salem&lt;/strong&gt;: Age: 16 Rank: ??? Class: ???&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ability: Chilly mist&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;™&lt;/span&gt;, ???&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Shoulder length white hair, white fur, blue eyes, pale skin, 5'0. Born on July 20th. Centauri fan number one!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calistra Katz&lt;/strong&gt;: Age 16 Rank: 3 Class: Hybrid Drago(Hidden)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ability: Heat manipulation&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Long yellow hair, red eyes, fair skin, 5'9. Born on April 16th. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rain Namona&lt;/strong&gt;: Age: 16 Rank: 3 Class: Hybrid(Alvine)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ability: Black flame&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Black feathered long silver hair, small black wings barely wider than her back, silver eyes, pale skin, 5'6. Anime addict.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Samantha Salem:&lt;/strong&gt; Age: ??? Rank: ??? Class: ???&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ability: ???&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Medium length black hair, brown eyes, fair skin, 5'10. Just an ordinary mother.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tiana Salem&lt;/strong&gt;: Age: ??? Rank: 5 Class: Star (Demigod)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ability: Enhanced telekinesis, Teleportation &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Long pitch black hair, blue eyes, pale skin, 5'11. The woman who broke the moon and the number one hero, Centauri. A not so ordinary aunt.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div class="wi_authornotes"&gt; &lt;div&gt; &lt;div class="p-avatar-wrap"&gt;&lt;a class="avatar has-link" href="/profile/139846/yulayulna/"&gt;&lt;img id="acc_ava_change profile" alt="" src="https://cdn.scribblehub.com/avatar/s/34/ava_139846_1705014170.jpg"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="an_username"&gt;&lt;a href="/profile/139846/yulayulna/"&gt;YulaYulna&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div style="clear: both;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="wi_authornotes_body"&gt; Not everything will go into the glossary chapters, though occasionally I'll add information as it appears in the story. Most of what's posted here will be what &lt;em&gt;Lily knows&lt;/em&gt; so as to circumvent spoiling. Take everything with a grain of salt, but also don't outright dismiss information. ??? isn't necessarily me being cryptic or hinting at future events, though sometimes that will be the case, instead it just means Lily simply doesn't know the information that should appear there. I know this seems a little sparse right now, but there's only ten chaps out so... yeeeaah. Good Wednesday to all, sorry for this just being a glossary and not an real chapter! &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
